        "Target status and progress made towards target": "Underway - moderate progress made",
        "Please explain": "Our four major decarbonisation strategies are “net-zero electricity generation”, “energy saving”, “green transport” and “waste reduction”. \\n\\nNet-zero electricity generation” - Other than the targets and progress mentioned in Target 2 (i.e. 2035 mid-term target), we will increase the share of RE in the fuel mix of electricity generation to 15% gradually, and achieve net-zero carbon emissions in electricity generation before 2050. \\n\\n“Energy saving and green buildings” - As mentioned in Target 2 (i.e. 2035 mid-term target),Our goal is to reduce the electricity consumption of commercial buildings by 30% to 40% and that of residential buildings by 20% to 30% from the 2015 level by 2050; and to achieve half of the above targets by 2035. \\n\\n “Green transport” -Other than the targets and progress mentioned in Target 2 (i.e. 2035 mid-term target), we strive to achieve the long-term target of zero carbon emissions in the transport sector before 2050 by promoting new energy transport and improving traffic management measures.\\n\\n ”Waste reduction” - As mentioned in Target 2 (i.e. 2035 mid-term target), the government will continue developing waste-to-energy facilities and promoting waste reduction and recycling, which can help achieve “zero landfill” by 2035. \\n\\n\\nSupplementary note to 6.1.1.18:\\nNet zero of total GHG emissions comparing with 2005\\n"
