        "Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Storm|Hurricanes, cyclones, and/or typhoons|Coastal flooding (incl. sea level rise)|Heavy precipitation|Urban flooding",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "To adapt to climate change and cater for increasing urbanisation, we have been actively commissioning the review studies on Drainage Master Plan (DMP), implementing flood prevention projects, incorporating environmentally friendly measures and promoting blue-green infrastructure. \\n\\nThe Contingency Plan for Natural Disasters sets out Government's strategy, organizational framework and the relevant alerting system, which will be subject to regular review. On-going regular inter-departments and stakeholders exercise drills which are aim to enhance the preparedness and responsiveness of B/Ds in natural disasters \\n\\nTo monitor the traffic and transport situation, liaise with stakeholders for emergency arrangements and recovery action; and issue advice to keep the media and the public informed of the latest situation.\\n\\nAutomatic flood risk alerts for government users regarding any anticipated flood risk due to heavy rain via dedicated GIS portals and email notification. The flood risk assessment service has been in trial use since May 2024. Enhancement of the service was carried out in December 2024. Development work with including real-time flood data is on-going. HKO will issue SMS storm surge alert messages to relevant government departments. District Offices will inform local residents and property management offices to take appropriate preparatory and precautionary measures. \\n\\n",
