    "q3_2": [
      {
        "question_text": "Does your jurisdiction have a consumption-based emissions inventory to measure emissions from consumption of goods and services? The consumption-based approach captures direct and lifecycle GHG emissions of goods and services and allocates GHG emissions to the final consumers, rather than to the producers.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Response",
        "Does your jurisdiction have a consumption-based emissions inventory?": "Yes, our jurisdiction has a consumption-based emissions inventory to measure emissions from consumption of goods and services",
        "Attach your consumption-based inventory, along with any supporting documents": "3-2-2_CarbonFootprintReport_Intercontinental0606.pdf,3-2-2_InterConStatement.pdf,3-2-3_AccommodationService.pdf,3-2-3_SimaProFactors.xlsx",
        "Provide an overview of your consumption-based inventory, including URL links, if applicable, along with any supporting methods/calculations": "The \\'Carbon Footprint Inventory Report for Accommodation Service (per room per day) (Deluxe Classic Room - King Bed 10 pings)\\' of InterContinental Kaohsiung Hotel is based on the requirements of the ISO 14067:2018 standard and “the Key Points for Promoting Product Carbon Footprint Management” by Taiwan's Environmental Protection Administration of the Executive Yuan(current name: Ministry of Environment) as per Attachment 3-2-3_AccommodationService. The hotel commissioned Afnor International Co., Ltd. to conduct external verification of the carbon footprint report. On-site verifications were carried out on May 21-24, 2024, and June 6-7, 2024, to confirm that the carbon footprint data complies with the Guidelines for Calculating the Carbon Footprint of Products and Services.\\nThe inventory data is in Attachment 3-2-3_InterconinventoryS2. This inventory uses the life cycle assessment tool “SimaPro v9.4.0.2,” with the database “Ecoinvent 3” (in Attachment 3-2-3_SimaProFactors). The life cycle impact assessment methodology follows the IPCC 2021 GWP 100a (incl. CO2 uptake) v1.00 greenhouse gas emission evaluation method, calculating the carbon dioxide equivalent from raw material extraction to the waste stage (cradle to grave, B-2-C). For this service, InterContinental Kaohsiung Hotel provides the \\'Deluxe Classic Room - King Bed (10 pings) per room per day\\' accommodation service, and all greenhouse gas emissions are fully included in the calculation without excluding any items.\\nHowever, the inventory belongs to the InterContinental Kaohsiung Hotel and hence is confidential, we cannot upload the inventory. The attachments include all supporting methods, carbon footprint report and 3rd party verification statements."
      }
    ],
