        "Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "Number of removed alien species. In 2023, 234 banded bullfrogs, 147 Hong Kong whipping frog, 87 zebra doves, and 5,052 green iguanas were successfully removed. Additionally, 15.2 hectares of bitter vine and lesser snakeroot, 12 hectares of river tamarind, 0.5 hectares of Santa Maria feverfew, and 1.0 hectares of Mimosa pigra L. were removed. (Data link https://orgws.kcg.gov.tw/001/KcgOrgUploadFiles/458/relfile/76950/63498/65f78e8b-3c66-4152-ba1f-b732f9c4af78.pdf )",
        "Comment": "In the future, the Agriculture Bureau will continue to reduce the number of green iguana hotspots in the City and completely remove green iguanas from closed urban areas. Besides green iguanas, the removal of invasive fauna and _ora will also continue to prevent their spread. Public education on fauna and flora will be promoted to raise awareness among the public about the harm and impact of invasive species on native biodiversity. The responsibilities of land management agencies will be strengthened to effectively implement the removal of invasive species. https://orgws.kcg.gov.tw/001/KcgOrgUploadFiles/458/relfile/76950/63498/ac9f0f7d-db5a-451e-86f8-0f856bcb2336.pdf"
