        "Provide a link, if applicable, and highlight any specific action the jurisdiction is implementing to reduce emissions from the consumption of goods and services in this category": "https://energypark.org.tw/energy-smartcity/page/download/show.aspx?num=16&kind=8 \\nThis project is consists of two main components: the foundation of energy conservation and place-based implementation. Each component includes specific execution strategies. For the energy conservation foundation, the main tasks include conducting research and surveys on energy consumption, enforcing energy-saving legislation, developing energy-saving strategies in collaboration with civic groups, demonstrating and promoting energy-efficient technologies, as well as establishing dedicated organizations and personnel for implementation. Through these efforts, the city aims to gain deeper insights into Kaohsiung's energy data and electricity usage patterns, while incorporating mechanisms for public participation to collaboratively establish effective energy and electricity-saving strategies tailored for the city.\\nAs for the place-based component, the primary actions include training energy-saving volunteers and promoting conservation awareness, conducting energy-saving education and demonstration programs, encouraging widespread public participation in energy-saving campaigns, and providing support to energy-vulnerable populations. These initiatives aim to activate and expand the role of Kaohsiung's energy-saving volunteer teams, allowing them to contribute meaningfully to the community. At the same time, diverse methods of energy education and advocacy will help foster a positive environment and social atmosphere for citywide energy conservation. Furthermore, care for energy-vulnerable groups will be strengthened, gradually moving the city toward the goal of achieving energy justice.\\n"
