        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Kaohsiung City is actively developing a diversified water supply. Since 2013, the city government has promoted the recycling and reuse of discharged water. Reclaimed water sourced from sewage regeneration is not affected by weather conditions, allowing each drop of water to be used at least twice and maximizing water resource utilization. This helps ensure industrial water supply and reduces pressure on water scheduling during dry periods.\\nThe Fengshan Wastewater Treatment Plant, Taiwan's first public wastewater reclamation facility, began supplying 45,000 CMD (cubic meters per day) in 2019 and expanded to 50,000 CMD in May 2024. The Linhai Wastewater Treatment Plant, the second national-scale reclamation project, began operations in 2022 with 33,000 CMD, and expanded to 50,000 CMD in May 2024. Together, the two plants supply 83,000 CMD of reclaimed water to the Linhai Industrial Zone, with full capacity reaching 110,000 CMD, significantly reducing industrial water stress.\\n\\nKaohsiung continues to promote the North Kaohsiung Reclaimed Water Project, including Qiaotou and Nanzi. The Qiaotou facility is expected to begin supplying 30,000 CMD in 2026. The Nanzi facility is scheduled to supply 20,000 CMD in 2028, expanding to 70,000 CMD by 2030.\\nAdditionally, backup groundwater wells currently supply 130,000 CMD, and the Liling underflow water project, scheduled for completion in July 2025, will add another 100,000 CMD. Through this multi-source water management approach, Kaohsiung City is reducing its vulnerability and exposure to increasingly frequent droughts. \\n",
