        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "China Steel Corporation's (CSC) has began to perform cogeneration and phasing out coals from boil. Their 2030 carbon reduction strategy has four key directions: adding direct reduced iron (DRI) to blast furnaces, injecting hydrogen-rich gas, increasing the use of scrap steel, and steel-chemical co-production. Among these, the steel-chemical co-production project, in collaboration with the Industrial Technology Research Institute (ITRI), completed the first-phase pilot line in 2023. This initiative aims to capture and purify CO and CO2 generated during the steelmaking process, to be used as a carbon source for the petrochemical industry to produce acetic acid, methanol, and other chemicals. The second-phase demonstration line is currently undergoing feasibility assessment, with an estimated annual carbon reduction of 240,000 tons. CSC plans to collaborate with downstream petrochemical companies and establish Dalinpu Carbon Circular Park, aiming to achieve commercialization by 2040 and mass-produce low carbon/green chemicals, with an anticipated annual carbon reduction of 2.9 million tons.\\nhttps://ksepb.kcg.gov.tw/ActivitiesDetailC001100.aspx?Cond=c6b1226f-15f4-48fa-bd2c-c99721f39bf2, \\nhttps://www.cepo.org.tw/PageContent.aspx?uid=07f59dac-acde-48c1-8253-46c116cccf8d",
