        "Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Stationary energy: Wastewater to energy initiatives",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "The Water Resources Bureau stated that the National Land Surveying and Mapping Center has provided a subsidy of NT70 million to replace energy-consuming facilities at the Qimei Plant with energy-efficient equipment. Additionally, a solar photovoltaic system will be installed for solar power generation. Through this carbon-neutral improvement project, the plant is expected to reduce annual greenhouse gas emissions by 517,974 tons of CO2. The project is currently in the design phase and is still implementing until January 2025. \\nThis project is mainly executed through three aspects: replacing old equipment with new, generating new energy, and implementing smart control. By replacing low-energy, high-efficiency equipment, the project aims to significantly reduce the plant's electricity consumption. Additionally, solar panels installed at the facility will provide electricity for the plant, with any excess green energy being used for carbon credit transfer at the Central Wastewater Treatment Plant. This will ultimately enable the plant to achieve zero carbon emissions, helping to meet the 2030 carbon reduction target. https://wrb.kcg.gov.tw/ActivitiesDetailC001100.aspx?Condf00e01f8-f569-479d-b58e-090f213e44ae, PS: budget information: https://web.pcc.gov.tw/tps/atm/AtmAwardWithoutSso/QueryAtmAwardDetailHist?fkPmsMainHistOTMyNDI0MTU\\n",
