        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "China Steel Corporation (CSC) located in Kaohsiung City is planning its 2050 net-zero pathway. In the 2030 phase, besides the co-production of steel and chemicals, there are several major strategies such as:\\n1. Intelligent Blast Furnace: Blast furnace ironmaking is the core process of steel mills. In the past, it was difficult to grasp the state of iron ore reduction reactions. After introducing 27 intelligent modules like ALoT (including 8 intelligent operation guidelines, 5 intelligent furnace condition indicators, 5 online intelligent diagnostics, and 9 intelligent prediction modules), combined with AI decision support, annual fuel costs can be reduced by 235 million NTD, and achieve an annual emission reduction of 11,346 tons.\\n2. Blast Furnace Injection of Hydrogen-Rich Gas: By using hydrogen-rich gas COG (Coke Oven Gas) to replace part of the pulverized coal, emissions are reduced. CSC has innovatively developed technologies such as tuyere image monitoring, blast flow rate, pressure difference, furnace top hydrogen concentration, and developed numerical simulation analysis of gas flow field and temperature distribution in the raceway zone. Injecting each ton of COG can reduce CO₂ emissions by 1.9 tons. It is expected to begin online testing in 2024, with an estimated emission reduction potential of 660,000 tons of CO2e.\\n3. Flue Gas Carbon Capture: CSC is developing efficient and low-energy carbon capture technology, establishing a pilot flue gas carbon capture plant expected to complete construction in 2024, with an annual carbon capture capacity of 500 tons.\\n4.*Increasing Scrap Steel Use in Converters: By increasing the proportion of scrap steel through technologies such as heat compensation in steelmaking, rapid melting of scrap steel, and temperature rise in secondary refining, carbon emissions can be reduced.\\n\\nhttps://www.csc.com.tw/csc/esg/env/env1.html, \\nCSC's report at the 2024 Southern Taiwan Summit: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=49MSAG2Y8RE",
