        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Since 2021, CPC Corporation, Taiwan has allocated a budget of 8.7 million NTD to execute a project for the construction of experimental equipment for carbon capture and methanol conversion. In the short term, it plans to establish experimental equipment at the Dalin Refinery of the Refining Business Division, capable of capturing at least 20 kilograms of CO₂ per day (6 tons of CO₂ per year) and converting CO₂ into methanol with a production capacity of at least 3 kilograms of methanol per day (1 ton of methanol per year).\\nIt is expected that in 2022, the CO₂ capture unit experimental equipment will be set up at the Dalin Refinery, and by 2023, the construction of the CO₂-to-methanol conversion unit experimental equipment will be completed. By using CO₂ as a carbon source—capturing and converting it into methanol chemicals—a complete industrial chain for a CO₂ circular economy will be formed to facilitate significant carbon reduction. In the future, the company will develop preparation technologies such as new high-activity catalysts, ultimately applicable to small-scale demonstration sites for CO₂ capture and conversion into methanol.\\nIn the medium to long term, there are plans to introduce commercialized processes. It is projected that by 2030, the carbon capture capacity will reach 1 million tons per year, and the carbon reutilization capacity will reach 250,000 tons per year. By 2050, the carbon capture capacity is expected to achieve 3 million tons per year.\\nPS: Under the \\'Research and Development Expenditures\\' in 2023, CPC has continuously allocated 49.3 million NTD to carry out the project. Until the expected year(2050), the whole budget should be 49300000+8700000*30=310,300,000.\\nhttps://www.ly.gov.tw/Pages/Detail.aspx?nodeid=45976&pid=225346",
