        "Factors considered in assessment": "Assessment considers water security|Identified hazards have been incorporated into the jurisdiction's overall risk management framework|Assessment includes sectors and/or urban systems|A process has been established for prioritizing identified hazards|A process has been established to update the assessment at least every five years|Assessment considers vulnerable populations|Assessment considers nature",
        "Please explain": "The City has established the New Taipei City Regional Disaster Prevention and Relief Plan, which identifies disaster types within the jurisdiction, characteristics of various disasters, historical cases, disaster potential analysis (or surveys of disaster-prone populations), scenario simulations, disaster prevention and relief planning, mitigation measures, and public awareness campaigns. The plan is reviewed and revised every two years to ensure it accurately reflects the City's current disaster prevention and relief conditions.\\n"
