        "row_order": 2,
        "row_name": "Row 2",
        "Factors that affect ability to adapt": "Legal/Institutional constraints",
        "Degree to which this factor challenges/supports the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "Challenges: Significantly challenges",
        "Describe how the factor supports or challenges the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "In 2020, New Taipei City signed the “Climate Emergency Declaration” and, in 2021, established the “New Taipei City Climate Change and Energy Strategy Executive Committee.” In 2023, in response to the enactment of the Climate Change Response Act, the city reorganized the committee and established the “Climate Change Response Steering Group” to strengthen the city's mitigation and adaptation capacity for the next ten years. \\n\\nThe responsibilities of the Steering Group and its affiliated project teams are as follows:\\n\\n1.Climate Change Response Steering Group\\nThe Group is responsible for formulating New Taipei City's vision and strategies for addressing climate change and promoting energy transition. It deliberates on major climate and energy-related issues, encourages participation in national and international forums, and builds partnerships with global cities committed to similar goals.\\nIn addition, the Group coordinates cross-sectoral initiatives—such as energy efficiency improvement, smart transportation development, circular economy promotion, and resilient disaster risk reduction—aiming to reduce and manage greenhouse gas emissions. Ultimately, the goal is to build a city with robust adaptive capacity, a sustainable energy system, and shared benefits of high environmental quality.\\n\\n2. Project Team\\n(1) Energy Transition and Efficiency Enhancement Team: Upholding the principles of local energy governance and citizen participation, the team promotes a whole-of-society energy transition through public-private partnerships. It also prioritizes improving energy efficiency and rational use, and works to establish sustainable energy mechanisms.\\n(2)Smart Transportation Team: This team integrates advanced information and communication technologies into transportation infrastructure to enhance traffic safety and flow, improve public mobility, and reduce the environmental impacts of transportation.\\n(3) Circular Economy Team: From manufacturing at the source to consumption at the end, the team endeavors to increase “resource efficiency” and “recycling” while actively developing innovative consumption models to achieve co-prosperity in both environmental and economic dimensions.\\n(4) Resilient Adaptation Team: Guided by the three core concepts of “strengthening adaptation capacity,” “enhancing resilience,” and “reducing vulnerability,” the team aims to lessen the impacts and risks of climate change, respond effectively to disasters, and improve self-recovery capacity."
