        "row_name": "Response",
        "Percentage of households within the jurisdiction with access to clean cooking fuels and technologies^": ">75%",
        "Data source": "National-level data",
        "Year data applies to": 2024.0,
        "Comment": "Most households, restaurants, and public institutions in New Taipei City primarily use natural gas or liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) as cooking fuels for gas stoves.\\n\\nAccording to the Bureau of Energy, Ministry of Economic Affairs, the natural gas penetration rate in New Taipei City reached 63.54% in 2024. In addition, the LPG penetration rate was reported as 31.34% in 2023. Based on these figures, it is estimated that over 99% of households in the city have access to clean cooking fuels and technologies.\\n\\nBesides gas stoves, electricity is also commonly used as a cooking energy source. Electricity in Taiwan is centrally supplied and distributed by the state-owned Taiwan Power Company (Taipower), which ensures universal access to energy. According to Taipower's 2023 Sustainability Report, except for legal or regulatory restrictions, the company fulfills all electricity service applications, achieving a 100% service provision rate. As a result, nearly all households in the city are connected to the electricity grid, with the exception of a small number of low-income households."
