        "Comment": "1.Passenger transportation figures are calculated based on the original questionnaire data from the \\'2022 Survey of People's Daily Means of Transportation\\' conducted by the Ministry of Transportation and Communications (central government):\\n（1）Based on the “Modal Share of Trips Made by Residents of New Taipei City” statistics table, using the proportion of trips made by residents of New Taipei City.\\n（2）According to the existing data, it is currently not possible to break down the share of informal/feeder transport/mass transit systems in the total passenger transport modes; therefore, the value is entered as 0.\\n（3）In the statistical tables published by the Ministry of Transportation and Communications, ferries are categorized under “Other Modes of Transport,” and shared cars/motorcycles are categorized under “Private Vehicles.”\\n\\n2.Freight transportation was calculated based on the \\'2024 Freight Transportation Survey Report\\' conducted by the Ministry of Transportation and Communications, as well as the \\'2024 Volume of Goods Transported at Stations of the Taiwan Railways Administration\\':\\n(1)Motorcycles: There is no available data on freight transported by motorcycles. Additionally, it is not possible to distinguish whether motorcycles are used for delivery services. Therefore, this category is reported as zero.\\n(2)Trucks (small, medium, and large): Data on freight tonnage by trucks in New Taipei City were sourced from the 2024 Motor Vehicle Freight Survey Report. Based on vehicle-kilometer transport demand patterns, the tonnage was divided as follows: small trucks account for 66.7%, while medium and large trucks combined account for 33.3%.\\n(3)Rail Transport: Rail freight volume in New Taipei City was estimated by taking the total tonnage of goods \\'arriving at and dispatched from\\' stations within the city from the 2024 Taiwan Railways Statistical Yearbook and dividing by two. Since the yearbook only reports freight volumes by railway line rather than by station, the 2020 distribution ratios by station were used to estimate the breakdown for each station.\\n(4)No Inland Water Transport: There is no inland water transport system within the jurisdiction of New Taipei City."
