        "What factors affect your jurisdiction's ability to address the selected health issues": "Lack of financial capacity and expertise/technical capacity",
        "Comment": "Under climate change, rising temperatures and seasonal variations pose potential pressure on New Taipei City's infectious disease prevention and control system. High temperatures and hot, humid environments are conducive to the breeding of disease vectors, increasing the potential risk of vector-borne diseases such as dengue fever, especially in densely populated areas where environmental management is challenging. In addition, climate change may disrupt the original seasonal patterns of infectious disease outbreaks, making the deployment of monitoring, early warning, and prevention measures more difficult, thereby increasing the burden on the medical and public health systems. When an epidemic spreads widely, emergency resources, isolation beds, and the allocation of medical personnel will also face pressure, affecting the efficiency of medical emergency response."
