        "Progress made towards target": "The goal is to achieve 100% adoption of electric motorcycles in the public sector by 2030.\\nIn 2021, the total number of official motorcycles was 6,654, with 224 electric motorcycles, accounting for 3.36% of the total.\\nIn 2022, the total number remained at 6,654, with 383 electric motorcycles, representing 5.76%.\\nIn 2023, there were 551 electric motorcycles out of 6,654, accounting for 8.28%.\\nBy 2024, the number of electric motorcycles increased to 794, making up 11.93% of the total."
