        "Target type^": "Transport target: Target to increase low-carbon/electric vehicles in government fleet",
        "Target description": "The goal is to achieve 100% adoption of electric vehicles in the public sector by 2035. Based on the current electricity carbon emission factor, electrifying fuel-powered vehicles can reduce carbon emissions by approximately 50%. The city plans to prioritize the full electrification of official vehicles and gradually promote the transition to the private sector through public sector demonstration.\\n\\nStarting from 2022, the proportion of electrified official vehicles has increased annually, with all eligible fuel-powered vehicles being replaced by electric vehicles upon reaching the replacement threshold. By 2035, it is expected that, except for special-purpose vehicles, all aging official vehicles within the jurisdiction will have been phased out or replaced with electric vehicles.\\n\\nIn addition, to support the development of electric vehicles, the city is actively installing charging stations to reduce the vehicle-to-charger ratio (i.e., number of electric vehicles per charging station).",
