        "Progress made towards target": "The number of households connected to sewage pipes that collect domestic sewage for treatment at sewage treatment plants is expected to reach 1.38 million by 2030. By the end of 2022, the number had reached 1.17 million households, and by the end of 2023, it increased to 1.205 million households. As of the end of 2024, the number of households with sewage pipe connections reached 1.238 million."
