        "row_name": "Household appliances and electronics",
        "Response": "Yes",
        "Provide an attachment to the strategy addressing emissions from consumption of the most relevant goods and services": "住宅家電汰舊換新節能補助作業要點.pdf",
        "Provide a link, if applicable, and highlight any specific action the jurisdiction is implementing to reduce emissions from the consumption of goods and services in this category": "https://www.etax.nat.gov.tw/etwmain/tax-info/purchase-energy-saving-appliance-reduced-commodity-tax-refund-area \\n\\n\\'Energy saving\\' is the top priority in the government's net-zero carbon emissions blueprint. Since 2017, the City has been complying with the central government's new electricity saving campaign to promote electricity saving for residential and commercial purposes, and subsidizing the public to replace high electricity-consuming appliances such as air conditioners, refrigerators and dehumidifiers with products of first or second-level energy efficiency. At present, the central government subsidizes the refund of the goods tax of energy-saving home appliances, and encourages the public to use energy-saving home appliances."
