        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "In order to effectively monitor real-time water conditions in flood-prone areas, New Taipei City began constructing the “All-Disaster Intelligent Command and Monitoring Center” in 2018. The real-time monitoring system is used during the activation of the Emergency Operation Center (EOC) and features dynamic visualizations such as a disaster spot map and statistical dashboards to support commanders in decision-making. The system helps safeguard the lives and properties of residents in potential disaster areas and continues to be upgraded in stages.\\n\\nTo enhance technological capability, the EDP (Engineering Development Project) integrates three core technologies: Open API integration, automated web crawling, and spatial big data AI analysis. These upgrades significantly shorten the information compilation process from hours to just minutes by consolidating data from 150 sources. Using historical disaster data and future rainfall forecasts, the system can predict likely flood zones and proactively notify district offices to deploy disaster prevention resources. By leveraging information technology, the system reduces manpower needs and minimizes potential loss of life and property.\\n\\nLink:\\nBuilding New Taipei City's Integrated Smart Disaster Prevention and Relief Platform\\nhttps://wedid.ntpc.gov.tw/Governance/Detail/R7O8l7YjPyba",
