        "Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "River flooding|Heavy precipitation|Urban flooding|Hurricanes, cyclones, and/or typhoons",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "To improve and maintain the water quality of the Tamsui River system, New Taipei City has adopted a cross-agency watershed governance approach. This strategy incorporates pollution source control, engineering improvements, river corridor restoration, and end-point inspection and regulation. Through coordinated inter-agency collaboration and proactive policy measures, the city aims to completely eliminate severely polluted stretches of the river by 2030.\\n\\nBy 2024, the proportion of severely polluted river sections in the Tamsui River basin has been reduced to just 0.5%, marking the best water quality status in the river's history. The project has earned New Taipei City the highest rating—\\'Outstanding\\'—among Taiwan's six special municipalities in the Ministry of Environment's performance evaluation.\\n\\nEstablishing a River Environment Information and Pollution Early Warning Monitoring System (Restoring River Vitality)\\n1.Regulatory Framework:\\nWater Pollution Control Act, Stricter Effluent Discharge Standards for the Daan Canal Main Line (New Taipei City),Stricter Effluent Discharge Standards for the Taliao River and Its Tributaries (New Taipei City)\\n\\n2.Implementation Facilities:\\n(1) Adopt the \\'Six Waters\\' construction concept:\\nWater Safety, Water Clarity, Water Infiltration, Water Recreation, Water Ecology, and Water Culture,to enhance water governance and support ecological restoration of urban rivers.\\n(2) Install automated water quality monitoring stations at key river sections.As of September 17, 2021, three monitoring stations have been established at: Fuzhou Bridge, New Moon Bridge, and the Huajiang Floating Dock (Xindian River).\\nThese installations provide long-term data for building a comprehensive water quality big data platform.\\n\\n3.Management Measures:\\n(1) Review and approve pollution control plans and discharge permit applications.\\n(2) Conduct on-site inspections of pollution incidents and enforcement actions as necessary.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1.Department of Environmental Protection Department - Water Environment Monitoring Program Website https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article?catID=481 \\n\\n2.New Taipei City Excels in River Restoration, Ranked Best Among Six Special Municipalities in Water Pollution Control Evaluation\\nhttps://reurl.cc/6q5jvM",
