        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "To prevent the northward spread of dengue fever vector mosquitoes due to climate warming, New Taipei City has strengthened its dengue fever prevention and control efforts through the following measures:\\n1. Mosquito Vector Index Survey: Local health centers conduct surveys of the dengue vector mosquito index across all 1,032 administrative villages in the city. During the non-epidemic season, at least 10% of villages in each district are inspected, and during the epidemic season, at least 20% are surveyed. All 1,032 villages are inspected once per year to implement comprehensive vector mosquito monitoring, enabling early identification and treatment of high-density breeding areas.\\n2. Source Reduction and Public Awareness: The city has intensified efforts to eliminate breeding sources and strengthen public education on dengue prevention among community residents.\\n3. Early Case Detection and Rapid Diagnosis: By shortening the interval between symptom onset and diagnosis (targeting less than 3 days), the city aims to detect cases early and reduce the hidden period of confirmed cases reported by medical institutions, thereby preventing large-scale outbreaks.\\n\\nNew Taipei City actively implements the “Inspect,\\nEmpty, Clean, Scrub” measures to eliminate vector mosquito breeding sources and strengthen\\ncommunity awareness of dengue fever prevention. In 2024, a total of 17,306 breeding sources were eliminated. Early detection efforts resulted in 61.7% of cases being identified within less than 3 days of incubation.\\n\\nLink: \\n1.Department of Environmental Protection - Vector Control Information https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article?catID=1982\\n\\n2.Outcomes of Mosquito Breeding Sites Elimination Efforts\\nhttps://reurl.cc/DOblx5",
