        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "The Agriculture Bureau's Specific Measures and Content for Enhancing Natural Ecosystem Adaptation:\\n1.To enhance the ecosystem's capacity to respond to climate change, the Agriculture Bureau conducts ecological resource monitoring in the Wazihwei Nature Reserve to protect the mangrove ecosystem and reduce biodiversity loss.\\nFunding: NT$1.35 million per year. \\n2.To prevent biodiversity loss, the Agriculture Bureau provides long-term guidance to farmers transitioning from conventional farming to organic and eco-friendly practices. These practices avoid the use of chemical fertilizers, pesticides, and herbicides, aiming to protect the ecological environment, biodiversity, and promote sustainable use of resources. \\nFunding: NT20 million/year \\n\\nLinks: \\n1.Agriculture Bureau - Wazihwei Nature Reserve in Bali District https://www.agriculture.ntpc.gov.tw/information.php?p_id=55\\n\\n2.Agriculture Bureau—Production Guidance https://www.agriculture.ntpc.gov.tw/information.php?p_id=72",
