        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "New Taipei City plans to complete the construction of the “Three Rings and Six Lines” MRT network by 2030. The network will span a total length of 235 kilometers and cover most administrative districts of the city, integrating with the existing public transportation system. Diverse shared mobility services will be introduced around transit hubs and scenic areas, and shared vehicle parking spaces will be set up through mobility management strategies. These measures aim to increase the usage of public transportation and shared mobility options, while reducing the ownership rate of private vehicles. \\n\\nIn the “Total Cost of Action” field below, NT$18,377,940,000 is reported as the budget for the 2021-2025 period, covering the Taipei-New Taipei monthly MRT pass and part of the construction for the Three Rings and Six Lines MRT project. The budget for the Bali Light Rail Transit (LRT) project is still under deliberation.\\n \\nLinks: \\n1.Public Progress Page for the Three-Ring and Six-Line MRT Network\\nhttps://www.dorts.ntpc.gov.tw/about \\n\\n2.New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620",
