        "Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Transportation: Electric vehicle charging points and infrastructure",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "The New Taipei City Government plans to improve the user environment for electric vehicles by promoting the installation of charging stations in residential, commercial, and public parking areas through regulatory measures. New buildings will be required to reserve space for future installation of charging stations, and public parking lots must provide a certain proportion of EV charging spaces. In addition, the city will implement electric vehicle usage management strategies, including designating exclusive EV charging parking spaces and offering parking and charging rate discounts. \\n\\nElectrification of private vehicles will be promoted through a “subsidy-first, regulation-later” approach, in coordination with the implementation of air quality maintenance zones. By 2040, the sales share of electric cars and motorcycles is expected to reach 100%. By 2035, the logistics sector's motorcycles and tour buses will be fully electrified, and designated areas will restrict the use of fuel-powered motorcycles. In 2040, the city will expand these restrictions to cover fuel-powered cars and light trucks, and mandate full electrification of logistics cargo trucks. By 2050, all official vehicles and motorcycles will be fully electrified, with electric vehicles reaching a 60% market share. \\n\\nBefore 2030, all government motorcycles will be fully electrified. For large public service vehicles such as garbage trucks, recycling trucks, and city buses, the city will also evaluate the use of zero-carbon fuels such as biodiesel. \\n\\nIn the “Total Cost of Action” column below, NT$270,000,000 is reported as the budget for 2021-2025 to subsidize bus operators for the purchase of electric buses and to support citizens in replacing fuel-powered motorcycles with electric ones.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1.Department of Environmental Protection , New Taipei City Government - Toward the Net-Zero Carbon Goal: All Official Vehicles and Motorcycles to Be Fully Electrified by 2035\\nhttps://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9195 \\n\\n2.New Taipei Transportation Department -Shared Mobility Zone\\nhttps://www.traffic.ntpc.gov.tw/home.jsp?id=8c850d9caa7f43fc \\n\\n3.New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620",
