        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "For general waste, recyclable waste, and kitchen waste generated in New Taipei City, a sound recycling and reuse system will be established, and the resource recovery rate will increase year by year. Starting in 2030, the provision of disposable items and tableware will be prohibited. In addition to encouraging repeated use by consumers (user-end) and promoting recycling and remanufacturing by producers (supply-end) to create alternative raw materials, a reusable container system will be established. This will be supported by initiatives such as the “No-Plastic Customer” campaign, “Happiness Stations,” and the “Recycling Rewards Service System” to enhance recycling efficiency.. \\n\\nIn the “Total Cost of Action” field below, an amount of NT$1,005,710,000 is reported for the period 2021-2025. This includes expenses related to the paid garbage bag program, the Recycling Rewards Service System (which supports citywide recycling efforts), campus composting promotion, and the Green Circular Store Program, which assists restaurants and supermarkets in waste reduction. \\n\\nLinks: \\n1.Governance Achievement Network - Plastic-Free Living - Making New Taipei a Hub for Plastic Reduction\\nhttps://wedid.ntpc.gov.tw/Governance/Detail/r6W3vergP42O \\n\\n2.New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620",
