        "Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Stationary energy: Energy efficiency/ retrofit measures addressing existing commercial, residential and/or municipal buildings",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": " 1. Encourage buildings to install smart meters or micro-meters to collect household electricity consumption data, analyze residents' electricity usage patterns and energy consumption levels, and help guide the public toward energy-saving lifestyles.\\n\\n2. Promote the “Energy-Saving E-House” program to disclose the energy efficiency of residential community buildings and encourage property management companies to improve the energy performance of public facilities within communities. For communities with poor energy efficiency, the city government's “Power-Saving Clinic” team can provide on-site diagnostics and energy-saving recommendations. The city also offers a “Low-Carbon Community Retrofit Subsidy” program to support energy-saving improvements in such communities.\\n\\n3. Promote “Performance Specifications for Building Power Equipment” and establish “Carbon Neutrality Standards” for public buildings, giving priority to subsidies or low-interest financing for buildings that adopt green building materials, renewable energy, or green construction methods.\\n\\n4.In the public sector, establish a “Smart Energy Management Center” for government agencies, requiring institutions and schools to continuously engage in energy efficiency management. It is expected that all institutions and schools will meet EUI standards by 2030.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1.New Taipei City Low-Carbon Living Network - Energy-Saving E-House Project https://wedid.ntpc.gov.tw/Governance/Detail/WwkvADROlBJx \\n\\n2.Governance Achievement Network - Nation's First Smart Energy Community https://wedid.ntpc.gov.tw/Governance/Detail/06YdLE6klR7b \\n\\n3.New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620\\n\\n4.Bottom-Up Net-Zero Action: New Taipei City's Low-Carbon Community Grant Offers Up to NT$400,000\\nhttps://reurl.cc/damWEy\\n\\n5.Municipal News — New Taipei Leads the Nation: Mayor Hou Yu-ih Launches Smart Energy Management System for School Air Conditioning\\nhttps://reurl.cc/9nRpyv",
