        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Bottom ash from waste incineration is used as recycled aggregate, with a planned annual supply target of 100,000 metric tons to replace natural sand and gravel, achieving a carbon reduction potential of approximately 158 metric tons per year. In addition, the heat generated from incineration is used for power generation, and the electricity sales rate of incineration facilities will be continuously improved, with carbon capture technology also to be introduced.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1. Department of Environmental Protection, New Taipei City Government - Recycling Process and Quality Control https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article?catID=1862 \\n\\n2. New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620",
