        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "(1)Promote local agricultural products to reduce the carbon footprint generated during the transportation of agricultural goods.\\n(2)Implement the “Eco-Friendly Farmland Regional Plan” and provide subsidies for organic materials to enhance soil carbon sequestration through eco-friendly and organic farming practices, while preserving environmental quality and ecological conservation.\\n(3)Promote urban afforestation and planned tree planting, encourage participation from civil society organizations, and facilitate corporate-sponsored tree planting in schools. The city plans to plant one million trees, shrubs, or groundcover plants each year to increase carbon sinks. In 2024, Far Eastern Department Stores supported the initiative by planting 40 Calocedrus formosana and 700 native Taiwan lilies at Wensheng Elementary School.\\n(4)Promote the “New Taipei Mountain and Coastal Afforestation Project”, which involves tree planting on land and along the coast. For terrestrial areas, the city plans to plant 40,000 trees annually.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1.Diverse Tree Planting, Ecological Sustainability\\nhttps://wedid.ntpc.gov.tw/Governance/Detail/753P4wjnvZkV\\n\\n2. New Taipei Promotes Urban Afforestation and Facilitates Corporate Adoption of School Tree Planting to Fulfill ESG Goals\\nhttps://www.ntpc.gov.tw/ch/home.jsp?id=28&dataserno=202403220026\\n\\n3.New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620",
