        "Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Generation of grid-supplied energy: Optimize traditional power/ energy production",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "New Taipei City has suspended the issuance of new bituminous coal permits since 2016. In 2019, it completed two major policies: phasing out coal-fired boilers and replacing fuel oil with gas in the asphalt industry. The city plans to convert all coal- and oil-fired boilers to natural gas as a transitional alternative, and further aims to phase out natural gas by 2045.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1. Governance Achievement Network - Ranked No. 1 Nationally; New Taipei Officially Joins the Powering Past Coal Alliance https://wedid.ntpc.gov.tw/Governance/Detail/2OZgPqJgLDA4 \\n\\n2. New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620",
