        "Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Industrial Processes and Product: Improve energy efficiency of industrial processes",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "New Taipei City has introduced energy monitoring and management systems in industrial processes, and promotes two main directions: inspection and improvement.\\n\\n1.Inspection: For large energy consumers—those with increasing electricity consumption, annual energy savings below 1%, or an energy use intensity (EUI) above the average—regular on-site inspections are conducted, along with annual random audits. These users are required to achieve at least a 1% annual electricity savings. For small energy consumers (with contracted capacity between 100 and 800 kW), energy-saving and carbon-reduction diagnostic services are provided, along with specific improvement suggestions.\\n\\n2.Improvement: The city matches large energy consumers with energy service providers to offer energy-efficient equipment upgrade plans at prices below the market rate. Energy-saving specifications are being developed for such equipment. In collaboration with the central government, subsidies are provided for major industrial power equipment—such as pumps, fans, and air compressors—to help factories propose energy-saving and carbon-reduction plans. The city also encourages the development of hydrogen energy technologies for integration into industrial processes.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1. Website of Energy Administration, Ministry of Economic Affairs - Large Electricity Consumer Rule Comes into Effect; New Taipei City's “Energy-Saving Professional Service Team” Offers Free Diagnostics https://energy.csd.org.tw/mooc/energy/news/info_content.php?type=3&id=1063 \\n\\n2.Large Electricity Consumers Save 34.73 Million kWh Annually; New Taipei's Energy-Saving Service Team Invites You to Join the Effort \\nhttps://reurl.cc/Mzybzv\\n\\n3. New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620",
