        "Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Transportation: Improve walking, cycling and integrated transit access",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "To improve the cycling environment and increase bicycle usage, New Taipei City's total length of bicycle lanes reached 691.1 kilometers by the end of 2024, reflecting a 1.5% increase compared to 680.48 kilometers at the end of 2023. A total of 14,420 bicycle racks have been installed across the city. The expansion of bicycle lane length primarily occurred in Shulin, Yingge, and Ruifang districts, as well as along the Dahan River cycling system.\\n\\nLooking ahead, the city will further connect riverside bicycle lanes with urban routes to create a “green commuting corridor,” and strengthen the deployment of public bicycle services in surrounding areas. For existing bicycle infrastructure, efforts will focus on enhancing route continuity, improving pavement visibility at intersections to ensure cycling safety, and incorporating barrier-free design to safeguard the rights of all road users. With a well-developed cycling environment and accessible shared bicycle services, New Taipei City aims to achieve a 5.5% bicycle modal share by 2050.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1. Transportation Department - Governance Planning: Establishing a People-Oriented Green Transportation Environment https://www.traffic.ntpc.gov.tw/home.jsp?id=b757fa8d7920d37f\\n\\n2. New Taipei City 2050 Net Zero Roadmap and Climate Action White Paper https://www.epd.ntpc.gov.tw/Article/Info?ID=9620",
