        "Identified financing model": "Grants|Public finance- national government|Public finance- own budget",
        "Project description and URL link, if applicable": "To achieve the policy objectives of energy conservation, carbon reduction, and environmentally friendly green transportation—thereby creating a more comfortable transportation and living environment—the New Taipei City Government aligns with the Executive Yuan's 2017 policy of “Full Electrification of Urban Buses by 2030.” Bus operators are encouraged to purchase electric buses, and the city is actively considering increasing the subsidy amount for replacing conventional buses with low-floor electric buses, while also seeking subsidies from the Ministry of Transportation and Communications.\\n\\nIn 2011, the New Taipei City Government enacted the Green Bus Subsidy Rules and introduced Taiwan's first electric bus. The rules stipulate subsidy regulations for electric buses and clean-fuel buses powered by natural gas, dual-fuel systems (oil and gas), hybrid systems (oil and electricity), and hydrogen, among others, to accelerate the phase-out of diesel-powered buses. As of the end of 2024, there were 302 electric buses operating in New Taipei City. From 2022 to 2025, it is projected that 40 additional electric buses will be added each year.\\n\\nLinks: \\n1.All 656 Bus Routes Fully Electrified: New Taipei City's Largest Electric Bus Network\\nhttps://www.ntpc.gov.tw/ch/home.jsp?id=28&dataserno=202302230038\\n\\n2.New Taipei City Government Guidelines for Subsidies on Urban Green and Eco-Friendly Public Bus Purchases https://www.rootlaw.com.tw/LawArticle.aspx?LawID=B020240001005500-1001110 \\n\\n3. Subsidy Guidelines for the Electric Bus Demonstration Program (MOTC) https://www.mvdis.gov.tw/webMvdisLaw/LawArticle.aspx?LawID=I0197000 \\n\\n4. Operational Guidelines for Subsidizing Electric Buses under the Highway Public Transportation Program by MOTC https://www.rootlaw.com.tw/LawContent.aspx?LawID=A040110051001000-1090729",
