        "Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "颱風是對台灣影響最大的自然災害。 據統計，每年有3至5次颱風襲擊台灣。 颱風的暴雨造成的災害最多。 屏東是台灣颱風重災區。 屏東大雨造成的直接災害包括水災和山區土石流，以及登革熱、停電等間接災害。未來，由於氣候變化，颱風會變小、變慢、變強，暴雨的後果會更加嚴重。 大多數年輕人轉移到工作機會更多的城市地區，而老人和兒童則留在自然災害風險更高的山區。 颱風經常導致山區樹木倒塌和停電。 長者和孩童無法出門，只能在沒有電的情況下生活。A typhoon is a natural disaster that affects Taiwan the most. According to statistics, 3 to 5 typhoons hit Taiwan every year. The heavy rain of the typhoon causes most disasters. Pingtung is the region most frequently hit by typhoons in Taiwan. The direct disasters caused by heavy rain in Pingtung include floods and landslides, and indirect disasters such as dengue fever, power shutdown. In the future, due to climate change, typhoons will be lesser, slower, and stronger, so the aftermath of heavy rain will be more serious. Most of young people move to urban areas with more work opportunities, while the elderly people and children are left in mountainous area with higher risk of nature disasters. Typhoon often causes tree collisions and power outage in mountainous areas. The elderly people and children can't go out and have to live their lives without electricity supply.",
