        "Comment": "In the past, Pingtung County was lack of medical resources and residents had to seek medical treatment in other cities. About 6,000 patients annually require referrals for medical treatment on average. After completing Pingtung branch of Kaohsiung Veterans General Hospital in 2022, E-DA Hospital has also been constructing branch in Pingtung County. Residents do not need to cross the Gaoping River for medical treatment in the future, and also have more job opportunities. Bsides, Hengchun Peninsula is located at the southernmost tip of Taiwan. To strengthen the critical care capabilities of Hengchun Peninsula and improve the quality of emergency medical transportation, the County Government cooperates with medical centers to assist Hengchun Tourim Hospital, Hengchun Christian Hospital, and Nanmen Hospital in upgrading their emergency care and supplementing doctor manpower to prevent patients from going north and south for medical treatment and save precious time for treatment. By vertically integrating the Hospital Branches, local hospitals, and local medical facilities, Pingtung County provide comprehensive medical care for not only citizens in urban areas, but also residents in the southern Pingtung region, remote areas, and outlying islands, enhancing medical capacity and cross-district medical care."
