        "Target year of goal^": 2050.0,
        "Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "Responding to “Climate Change Response Act” enacted by central government, Pingtung County Government plans adaptive targets to build a low-carbon city with resilience to face climate change.1.Realize the distribution of vulnerable people and assist them to hold disaster prevent and rescue drills.2.Enhance resilience to face climate change by smart agricultural technology 3.Reduce climate risk and agricultural damage by disaster prevention and control systems.4.Improve warning system to stabilize the supply of agricultural products and seafood by adjusting farmers' and fishers' industrial management.5.Enhance and manage water and soil conservation of slope areas.6.Revitalize rural areas with resilience to face climate change.7.Announce “geologically sensitive areas” based on “Geology Act” as the basis of land utilizations, development examinations, disaster prevention and relief, environmental conservation, and natural resources development. 8.Enhance water management facilities, for example, basic infrastructures and designs for flood prevention9.Replace cables on electric poles with underground electric cables to enhance resilience of electric infrastructures.10.Complete disaster prevention information systems of mountainous areas to enhance their adaptative ability.11.Complete safety check and maintenance of bridges and arterial roads regularly12.Increase water resilience by various water resources and water management.13.Stabilize water supply to realize social justice.14.Enhance social welfare and safety network for the vulnerable group to reduce damage caused by climate disasters.15.Complete shelters and disaster prevention instructions in indigenous tribes to enhance resilience and energy autonomy.16.Enhance medical services for island areas by increasing ambulance ships and virtual appointments.",
