        "Select a reference ID for the goal": "Adaptation goal 12",
        "Adaptation goal^": "Health Care Receiving",
        "Climate hazards that goal addresses^": "Hurricanes, cyclones, and/or typhoons|Infectious disease",
        "Base year of goal (or year goal was established if no base year)^": 2018.0,
        "Target year of goal^": 2025.0,
        "Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "由於氣候變化，琉球地區孤島概率增加。 為保障居民生計，向內地醫院求助。 專家們將輪流支持門診醫療服務，通過Skype系統滿足當地的醫療需求。 琉球島是全台唯一有救護船的市鎮。 救護艇可承受7級風暴。 2020年，緊急醫療運送251人次，回家安寧19次，共計270人次。Due to climate change, the probability of island isolation in the Liuqiu area has increased. In order to protect the livelihood of the residents, the hospital from the mainland is consulted for assistance. The specialists will take turns to support outpatient medical services to meet the local medical care needs by using the Skype system. Liuqiu island is the only town in Taiwan that has an ambulance boat. The ambulance boat can withstand level 7 storms. In 2020, there were 251 emergency medical evacuation services, 19 times of home returning services."
