        "Target status and progress made towards target": "Underway - moderate progress made",
        "Please explain": "Pingtung County wants to achieve net zero emissions by 2050, which refers to the \\'Net Zero 2050: A Roadmap for the Global Energy Sector\\' published by the International Energy Agency (IEA) on May 18, 2021. If the county wants to achieve net zero by 2050, it is necessary to reduce 1.9 million tons (38%) of carbon emissions by 2030, and 3.5 million tons (70%) by 2040. Pingtung County government set short-term (2030), mid-term (2040) and long-term (2050) targets, the carbon reduction results can be 1.63 million tons in 2030 and 2.42 million tons in 2040. 1.7 million tons of carbon emission reduction is still needed, which will use forest carbon-sink and renewable energy as carbon offset to achieve the goal of net zero carbon emissions by 2050.<Residential>saving residential electricity, improving energy efficiency, and promoting net (near) zero buildings.Pingtung County has set Net Zero goals for buildings in 2030, 2040 and 2050. First, it is expected to make 85% of old buildings have the near-zero building mark in 2030, which can save about 730 million kWh of electricity and reduce 370,000 tons of CO2e.In 2040, Pingtung County will make 100% of old buildings become net-zero buildings, which can save about 830 million kWh of electricity and reduce 420,000 tons of CO2e. Moreover, Pingtung County will also promote the installation of solar photovoltaic panels on the roof of buildings, and 20% of electricity will be supplied by renewable energy, which will reduce 160,000 tons of CO2e.In 2050, Pingtung County estimates to achieve 100% net-zero buildings, which are expected to save 1.66 billion kWh of electricity and reduce 800,000 tons of CO2e.<Industry> replacing high-pollution boilers, integrating regional energy resources, and installing smart energy management systemsBy 2030, the full gasification of boilers can reduce 30,000 tons of emissions. Public institutions promote energy saving by 1% per year, which can reduce 150,000 tons of emissions per year.By 2040, carbon capture technology will capture 60% of carbon emissions, combined with energy saving of 1% every year, another 130,000 tons of carbon will be reduced.By 2050, factories will achieve net-zero goals by combining with zero-electricity carbon emission factor and carbon capture technology.<Transportation> increasing the coverage of public bicycles, electric vehicles, and promoting low-carbon public transportation*Charging station for electric car will be popularized in public parking spaces by 2030. Company vehicles will take the lead in electrification, and public transportation will be electrified by 2040, reducing 500,000 tons of CO2e. The vehicle will be fully electrified or the fuel will be converted to 100% green energy (including hydrogen energy), including aviation and shipping, which can reduce another 50,000 tons carbon emission by 2050.*The production of gasoline vehicles will be limited, and importing gasoline vehicles will also be prohibited from 2030 to 2040. Only electric vehicles can be sold after 2040 and then gasoline vehicles will be banned in 2050.<Renewable energy>increasing the installation of green energy facilities (1.5 GW), developing hydrogen energy and green electricity supply areaThe Pingtung County government has achieved 1 GW of renewable energy in 2022, reducing 820,000 tons of CO2e. In response to energy transition, the Pingtung County government expects to increase the amount of green energy to 1.25 GW by 2030 and 1.5 GW by 2040, reducing 1.23 million tons of CO2e.<Carbon offset>implementing carbon fixation and afforestation projects, promoting organic farming, and building carbon capture demonstration areaWith a view to increasing the amount of carbon sinks, Pingtung County continues to protect the existing forest in indigenous zone, and increases the area of wetlands. Stock farming aims at 100% utilization of excreta to reduce using chemical fertilizers. It is planned to prohibit chemical fertilizers by 2040. Furthermore, Pingtung County also put much efforts on producing biomass fuel from agricultural waste, and installing photovoltaic farms."
