        "Comment": "有鑑於本縣偏遠部落為用電不易又易受災的地區，常因強降雨爆發土石流，使聯外道路崩塌及電纜破壞，造而停電與通訊中斷，使救援及復電困難度提高。為減緩此困境，本府設置「自發自用型」防災型微電網，每處規劃由5.9 kW 太陽光電(10kW 混合型逆變器)、20 kW儲能電池、節能複合式管理控制系統與生質柴油發電機共同組成。 經評估，可連續不間斷使用72個小時，平時供應文化健康站或村辦公室電力，減少電費支出及碳排放量，無預警斷電或災變時，節能複合式管理控制系統可自動(亦可遠端與現場手動)轉換電力供給來源，維持基本照明、通訊及小型民生電器電力功能。There are many indigenous townships located in mountainous areas. Many tribes in these townships are prone to be affected by natural disasters. Mass movement caused by heavy precipitation results in traffic disruption and power outage, which is difficult for the rescue team to save victims and recover electricity supply. Consequently, Pingtung County Government sets up disaster prevention microgrid system (DPMS) to solve the problem. DPMS consists of 5.9 kW solar PV panels and 20kW batteries, which can supply electricity for 72 hours. DPMS can supply electricity for cultural centers, public health centers and township offices to reduce electricity bill and greenhouse gas emission in normal days and maintain emergency lights, communication and small domestic appliances during disasters."
