        "Current status of plan": "Implementation complete",
        "Boundary of plan relative to jurisdiction boundary": "Same - covers entire jurisdiction and nothing else",
        "Year of formal approval of plan": 2015.0,
        "End of year plan": 2018.0,
        "Comment": "屏東縣政府為將洪水期林邊溪多餘水量導引至人工湖內，利用該地區具備入滲效果佳的地質條件，補注至地下含水層，減緩因下游沿海地區過度抽取地下水造成地層下陷的速度。於104年推動大潮州人工湖第一期計畫，並已於107年正式完工，可供應每日約10萬立方公尺的地下水，不僅可減緩下游地區地層下陷情形，於乾旱期更可提供民生用水有效緩解旱象，兼顧涵養地下水層及水資源循環再利用之效果。第二期計畫，已於2024年6月送交政府審議，一旦第2期工程完工，每年可從林邊溪上游引地面水約1億5千萬立方公尺。\\n\\nIn order to store excess water from Linbian river during the flood period, the Pingtung County Government built Great Chaozhou Artificial Lake artificial lake based on the local feature. Great Chaozhou region has land with good water infiltration, which can refill underground water to slow down the land subsidence caused by excessive groundwater extraction in the downstream and coastal areas. The first-phrase project of Great Chaozhou Artificial Lake was launched in 2015 and was completed in 2018, which can supply about 100,000 cubic meters of groundwater every day. It can not only effectively alleviate drought by providing water for people's daily use, but also conserve groundwater and water resource recycling. The second-phrase project of Great Chaozhou Artificial Lake was submitted to the central government on June,2024. After completing the second-phrase project, it is estimated that 150 million of water can be refilled in the artificial lake.\\n"
