        "Select a reference ID for the action": "Adaptation Action 3",
        "Action^": "Engineered and built environment actions: Improved drainage",
        "Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Hurricanes, cyclones, and/or typhoons|Heavy precipitation",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "因應近年來氣候變遷導致極端降雨頻率增加，道路積淹水的情形容易影響用路人安全，為提升道路排水能力本府在施工上採取瀝青混凝土10cm、級配層50cm，共厚60cm，不僅可強化透水能力更提升道路品質，兩側設置長寬60cm*80cm道路側溝，增加道路排水通容斷面，增加水流宣洩量，目前本府因應地方需求等未來發展，先行於該區域新闢路段進行施作，完成後預計可提供開發設施之交通需求，且也成為聯外道路，未來將持續拓展至其他主要幹道改善民眾用路安全。\\nIn response to the increasing frequency of extreme rainfall caused by climate change in recent years, road flooding has become a concern for road user safety. To enhance drainage capacity, the county government has adopted a pavement structure consisting of 10 cm asphalt concrete and a 50 cm graded aggregate base, with a total thickness of 60 cm. This design not only strengthens permeability but also improves road quality. In addition, roadside ditches measuring 60 cm by 80 cm are installed on both sides to enlarge the drainage cross-section and increase water discharge capacity. At present, to meet local needs and future development, new road sections in the designated area are being constructed in advance. Once completed, these roads are expected to accommodate the transportation demands of development facilities and serve as external connecting routes. The government will continue to expand such improvements to other major roads, further enhancing traffic safety for the public. \\nLink:https://tw.news.yahoo.com/%E7%A7%91%E5%A4%A7%E8%B7%AF%E9%80%8F%E6%B0%B4%E9%8B%AA%E9%9D%A2%E5%B7%A5%E7%A8%8B-%E5%B1%8F%E7%A7%91%E5%A4%A7%E6%AA%A2%E6%B8%AC%E6%88%90%E6%9E%9C%E7%A0%94%E8%A8%8E%E6%9C%83%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B%E4%BE%86%E5%8F%96%E7%B6%93-114746562.html",
