        "Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Soil degradation/erosion",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "<小琉球潮間帶管理站>近年因氣候變遷、觀光興盛，致琉球海域生物量衰減、漁業資源資源枯竭，為永續經營自然生態資源、提升民眾保育觀念，本府滾動調整於今(114)年推動三大項保育管制措施，自年7月1日起新增蛤板灣潮間帶收取觀光保育費每名遊客60元(現有4潮間帶收取觀光保育費)、劃設「龍蝦洞核心區」禁止人員進入，並為避免混淆將海膽恢復為保育對象，希望與全民共同努力，保護珍貴的海洋資源。<Liuqiu Intertidal Zone Management Station>\\nIn recent years, climate change and the growth of tourism have led to a decline in marine biomass and the depletion of fishery resources in the waters around Liuqiu Island. To ensure the sustainable use of natural ecological resources and raise public awareness of conservation, the county government has introduced three major conservation control measures this year (2025). Beginning July 1, a conservation fee of NT$60 per visitor will be charged for the Haban Bay intertidal zone (in addition to the four intertidal zones where fees are already collected). Furthermore, the “Lobster Cave Core Zone” has been designated as a no-entry area, and sea urchins have been reinstated as a protected species to avoid confusion. Through these efforts, the government seeks to work hand in hand with the public to safeguard precious marine resources.\\nLink:https://www.cna.com.tw/news/aloc/202203220194.aspx",
