        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "<海岸環境污染防治>本府致力保護海洋生態環境，推動海洋垃圾清理、強化污染應變處置、志工招募及各項海洋管理政策，於2022年推動全國首創「海廢帶回 漁獲自肥」，截至2025年5月底已成功回收於120公噸之海洋廢義務，並招募環保艦隊累計1,372艘為全國第一，另邀集潛水志工組成潛海戰將清除海洋廢棄物，人數達274人。此外更成立國內第1支「潛海小戰將」，由墾丁國小13位高年級學生組成，經由潛水教練長期陪伴，深根海洋教育並指導潛水知識與技能，鼓勵孩童一起為永續海洋生態盡一份心力。\\n每年更落實海洋污染緊急應變演練及教育訓練，實際運用於海上漏油災害的即時應變處置，並結合海岸巡單位、安檢所及相關部門組成海洋污染緊急應變聯防體系，有效圍堵油污，防止污染擴大。\\n\\n<Costal environment pollution control>\\nThe county government is committed to protecting the marine ecological environment by promoting marine debris cleanup, strengthening pollution response measures, recruiting volunteers, and implementing various ocean management policies. In 2022, it launched the nation's first initiative, “Bring Back Marine Debris, Gain from Your Catch,” which by the end of May 2025 had successfully recovered 120 metric tons of marine waste. In addition, the county has recruited an “eco-fleet” totaling 1,372 vessels—the largest in the country—and organized 274 volunteer divers as an “Undersea Task Force” to remove marine debris. Furthermore, Taiwan's first “Junior Undersea Task Force” was established, composed of 13 upper-grade students from Kenting Elementary School. Under the long-term guidance of diving instructors, the children receive marine education and training in diving knowledge and skills, encouraging them to contribute to sustainable marine ecology.\\n\\nEvery year, the government also carries out marine pollution emergency drills and training, applying them to real-time responses in marine oil spill incidents. Together with coastal patrol units, inspection stations, and relevant agencies, a joint emergency response network has been established to effectively contain oil pollution and prevent oil from spreading.\\n\\nLink: https://www.pthg.gov.tw/News_Content.aspx?n=EC690F93E81FF22D&s=6BB73EA06000A896\\n",
