        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "<恆春半島銀合歡移除及復育造林計畫>\\n銀合歡原產自中美洲，民國65年引進薩爾瓦多銀合歡推廣種植，以供應紙漿用材，因生產成本較高，不受到市場青睞。但銀合歡憑藉強盛的結實及萌蘗能力，擴散至恆春半島內，改變了當地原生植群樣貌。銀合歡入侵降低生物多樣性，危害本土物種生存。\\n農業部林業及自然保育署屏東分署自90年初即開始規劃防治，將國有林地內的銀合歡以挖除或砍除的方式進行整治。104年起更結合各國、公有地經管機關投入防治工作，希望能更有效將恆春半島國、公有土地內景觀區、海岸林、交通要道旁分布密度高之銀合歡，分區階段性移除並復育造林，恢復半島原有植群景觀。\\n2023年國有土地銀合歡收購部分合計收購2,628餘公噸，私有地部分收購2,504餘公噸，合計5,132餘公噸。\\n\\n<Leucaena Removal and afforestation Project in Hengchun Peninsula>\\nLeucaena was imported from Central America in 1976 as pulp wood. However, Leucaena did not been used due to its high production cost. However, Leucaena widely spreads to the Hengchun Peninsula with its strong vital force, affecting the balance of the local ecological balance.\\nForestry and Nature Conservation Agency Pingtung Branch, Ministry of Agriculture, has launched the project of removing Leucaena in state-owned forests areas from 2000.\\nFrom 2015, Pingtung County Government keeps cooperating with other public sectors to expand the Leucaena removal project in public lands and afforest local trees to restore the and landscape of the peninsula\\nIn 2023, the County Government purchased 5,132 tons of Leucaena, including 2,628 tons from state-owned lands and 2,504 tons from private lands. \\n\\nLink:\\nhttps://pingtung.forest.gov.tw/0000352\\n",
