        "Areas collaboration focused on": "Natural environment|Ecosystem restoration|Forestry|Landscape and jurisdictional approaches",
        "Description of collaboration and any progress, if applicable": "Taichung City and Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co., Ltd. are collaborating on the \\'Urban Cooling Tree Planting Action Plan.\\' TSMC, based on its corporate social responsibility of \\'caring for the earth and thinking about the next generation,\\' is implementing environmental protection measures and promoting green sustainability. It has planted a large number of native Taiwanese and Taichung tree species in Taichung. In addition to cooperating on the Da'an Coastal Reforestation Project and planting hope seedlings in Wuri District, TSMC has also planted a green belt under the Highway 74 Overpass and invested tens of millions of yuan to optimize the section from Chaoma Road to Gongyi Road. The third phase of the 2014 plan will extend to the Yongchun Road section. It is expected that the greening work will be completed by the end of June 2015. The greening area will be approximately 17,950 square meters and the length will be 1,725 meters. The project will transform the landscape and environment, reduce carbon emissions and attract wind, and create a green corridor in Taichung.",
