        "Description of collaboration and any progress, if applicable": "In order to implement low-carbon policies and promote the sustainable development of green energy, we cooperate with schools, workers, associations and other units to provide vocational training and short-term vocational training and skill certification training for the unemployed. We plan to open courses such as \\'AI Smart Data Analysis and Green Energy Practice Application Class\\' and \\'Solar Photovoltaic Setting Level B License Class\\', as well as provide green energy related courses such as \\'ESG Green Leadership Sustainable Talent Training Class\\' and \\'Green Energy Industry Project Manager PM Training Class\\' for forward-looking industry talent training camps, to enhance people's awareness of sustainability and workplace skills, and cultivate green energy sustainable talents.",
