    "q2_1_1": [
      {
        "question_text": "Provide details on your climate risk and vulnerability assessment.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Row 1",
        "Assessment attachment^": "上傳_2.1.1_臺中市氣候變遷調適執行方案（核定本）.pdf",
        "Assessment direct link^": "1. Taichung City Climate Change Adaptation Strategy (PDF attachment)\\n2. Taichung City Land Development Plan（ https://reurl.cc/p6yDae ）\\n3. Taichung City Flood Risk Potential Area Preservation Plan（ https://reurl.cc/01OzKY ）\\n",
        "Confirm attachment/link provided to assessment": "The assessment has been attached and can be accessed (unrestricted) on the link provided",
        "Boundary of assessment relative to jurisdiction boundary^": "Same - covers entire jurisdiction and nothing else",
        "Year of publication or approval": 2024.0,
        "Factors considered in assessment": "Assessment considers transition risks|Assessment considers nature|Identified hazards have been incorporated into the jurisdiction's overall risk management framework|Assessment considers water security|A process has been established for prioritizing identified hazards|Assessment considers vulnerable populations|Assessment includes a high-emissions scenario (i.e., RCP 8.5)|A process has been established to update the assessment at least every five years",
        "Please explain": "1.\\tVulnerable groups:\\n(1)\\tDisaster sensitive areas: The adaptation plan will also consider the climate risks and vulnerabilities of each administrative region such as flooding, slope hazards, and drought.\\n(2)\\tSocioeconomic vulnerability (low-income families, unemployed, homeless, elderly, disabled, etc.)& Immigrants and ethnic minorities: may face higher risks as they may lack resources and capabilities to cope with the impacts of climate change. In the evaluation, attention should be paid to their vulnerability in terms of housing, economic situation, social security, and basic living needs.\\n(3)\\tHealth vulnerable groups (chronic disease patients, elderly, infants, pregnant women, etc.): Climate change may have greater negative impacts on their health. In the evaluation, attention should be paid to their vulnerability in terms of healthcare needs, emergency response capabilities, living environment, and other aspects.\\n2.\\tWater resource guarantee: Taichung City has a total of 6 water resource facilities, all located in the Dajia River basin. To protect water resources, catchment areas for reservoirs, as well as the Taichung City Tap Water Quality and Quantity Protection Zone.\\n3.\\tNatural environment protection: (1) Measures to respond to rising temperatures; (2) Mountain forest conservation, land use with low-impact development and eco-friendly concepts to develop mountain sightseeing and recreation industries and ecological natural landscape protection; (3) Introduce sponge cities concept to achieve a safe water environment; (3) Set up Taichung natural habitats, wildlife sanctuaries, and nature reserves, and regulate urban temperature through eight wind corridors to reduce the impact of the urban heat island effect; (4) Ecological protection of coastal resources and wetlands conservation.\\n4.\\tHigh emission scenario:\\n(1)\\tEvaluate the industrial structure and energy usage, and identify high-emission industrial and energy production enterprises to mitigate departmental emissions through process improvement.\\n(2)\\tConsider the transportation conditions, volume, and modes to evaluate the contribution of transportation to greenhouse gas emissions and promote improved public transportation to mitigate emissions.\\n(3)\\tExamining the energy efficiency of buildings, the use of renewable energy, and relevant policies to reduce carbon footprint.\\n(4)\\tThe evaluation may consider factors such as agricultural production methods, fertilizer use, and management of agricultural and livestock waste to assess their impact on greenhouse gas emissions.\\n5.\\tIncorporated identified disaster risks into the overall risk management framework of the city, promoting climate change disaster risk assessment and the designation of high-risk and potentially hazardous areas. For example, regular inspections of landslide and ground slip geological sensitive areas are conducted, promoting mountain slope conservation and disaster prevention, and strengthening slope stabilization projects for landslide prone slopes; In response to extreme rainfall, plan disaster relief and evacuation routes for disaster prone areas, replace roads for shelter and evacuation, inspect flooded hot areas, review urban design standards and strategic construction methods, develop and regulate building behavior in affected areas, evaluate building setback, channel width retention, first floor elevated buildings, foundation elevation, prohibition and restriction of construction, volume control and other restrictions. Improving public spaces, including reducing runoff, increasing permeable areas, constructing green belts, and adding flood detention spaces, to reduce the risk of flooding.\\n6.\\tEstablished a priority ranking process for identified disaster risks. As the climate change adaptation action plan involves all areas, to maximize the use of limited government resources, urgent, priority, and long-term planning are prioritized for each adaptation action plan. Through expert and scholar advisory team meetings, urgent actions in the disaster field.\\n7.\\tEstablished a process of updating evaluations at least once every five years, by the Climate Change Response Law. The climate change adaptation implementation plan is updated every four years, updating the adaptation content in various fields, and submitting annual results reports and reviews.\\n8.\\tAssess and consider transformation risks: \\'Taichung City Sustainable Net-Zero Autonomy Ordinance\\' adopts five categories: \\'zero-carbon industry\\', \\'zero-carbon environment\\', \\'zero-carbon transportation\\', \\'zero-carbon life and education\\', and \\'climate change adaptation\\' The college chapter accelerates the city's sustainable net-zero transformation, and sets up sub-laws such as a climate transition fund and incentives for citizens to implement the net-zero transformation. It continues to refine greenhouse gas reduction and climate change adaptation strategies, and accelerates sustainability achievement—net zero transition.\\n"
      }
    ],
