        "Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "1.\\tDrought has caused the suspension of agricultural irrigation, which may lead to food shortages, it affects the growth and yield of crops, causing farmers to face economic losses and livelihood difficulties.\\n2.\\tDrought causes the water level of the reservoirs to drop, greatly reducing the effectiveness of hydropower generation and limiting the water demand of residents, catering industry, tourism industry, and enterprises, especially in vulnerable communities where insufficient water storage equipment may cause difficulties in residents' lives.\\n3.\\tDrought has led to reduced water supply and regional water cuts, resulting in a decrease in factory production, forcing companies to restrict water use or seek alternative water sources, which may increase production costs and operational difficulties.\\n4.\\tWater shortage has led to a decrease in water levels in rivers and wetlands, which may cause dust pollution and endanger the balance and biodiversity of the local ecosystem. In addition, drought may trigger forest fires, causing damage to forest resources and ecosystems.\\n5.\\tClimate change, drought, and severe water scarcity may lead to food insecurity, malnutrition and inadequate nutrition among children in water-scarce areas, and water-related diseases are the leading cause of child mortality. Insufficient drinking water leads to illness and a large number of deaths among people who drink contaminated water. Cooking and personal hygiene are also affected, increasing the risk of infection. \\n6.\\tDrought leads to insufficient water resources, which affects the operation of medical institutions and postpartum care homes, especially for dialysis patients who require water. To this end, the city continues to provide guidance to hospitals, dialysis clinics, obstetrics and gynecology clinics, and postpartum care homes to strengthen relevant response measures, such as reserving at least 3 days of water storage to ensure uninterrupted medical and care services.\\n7.\\tThe impact of high temperatures and water shortages on ecosystems may lead to a reduction in biodiversity and disruption of ecological balance, which in turn may hinder agricultural and industrial development. Vulnerable communities (such as the elderly, children, and those with chronic diseases) are more susceptible to high temperatures, leading to heat stroke and other heat-related health problems, such as cardiovascular disease and respiratory problems.",
