        "Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "Slope disasters in Taichung City mainly occur in mountainous and hilly areas with steep terrain, fragile geology, and short and turbulent rivers, such as Heping, Dongshi, Xinshe, Taiping, and Beitun. There are 110 potential landslides in Taichung City, and most slope disasters are accompanied by typhoons and heavy rain. Vulnerable communities and industries may suffer the following impacts:\\n1.\\tResident safety: Residents living in areas susceptible to landslides may be forced to evacuate or suffer personal injury, especially in the absence of appropriate warnings and evacuation plans.\\n2.\\tHousing and infrastructure damage: Landslides may cause serious damage to housing and infrastructure. The erosion and accumulation of debris from landslides may destroy houses, roads, bridges, and other important infrastructure, leading to the loss of housing, road closures, and interruption of basic services for vulnerable communities.\\n3.\\tAgricultural and fishery losses: Landslides have a direct destructive effect on agriculture, with erosion and accumulation potentially damaging farmland and fishing grounds, destroying crops, fruit trees, and fishery facilities, resulting in income losses for farmers.\\n4.\\tDecline of tourism and service industries: The damage caused by landslides to tourist attractions and areas has led to the decline of tourism and related service industries. Landslide events may force the closure or restriction of tourist attractions, reduce the number of tourists, and thus affect local businesses and job opportunities. This has an economic impact on vulnerable communities and small businesses that rely on the tourism industry.\\n",
