        "Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "1.\\tThe flood-prone areas in Taichung City mainly include rivers such as Da'an River, Dajia River, and Wu River. Under extreme weather conditions, heavy rainfall often occurs, and special attention should be paid to the risk of landslides and floods in disaster-prone areas. Heavy rainfall has the greatest impact on indigenous peoples, low-income families, and marginalized/minority groups. For the general public, flooding of roads and houses also poses risks to property damage and life safety.\\n2.\\tDuring the flood season (May - November), heavy rainfall events and typhoons carrying frontal air currents result in inadequate drainage in the area, leading to flooding and obstruction of related roads, affecting the traffic. Surface runoff carrying soil and sand in the catchment area affects the water quality and turbidity of water storage facilities, resulting in the inability to supply water, indirectly affecting various water demand industries.\\n3.\\tExcessive rainfall may result in excessively wet soil, which may affect the growth and quality of crops. In addition, flooding and soil erosion may destroy farmland and crops, causing economic losses to farmers.\\n4.\\tSome low-lying areas in the city may experience flooding due to insufficient drainage caused by heavy rainfall or typhoons, which will affect the operation of factories.\\n5.\\tThe top priority of disaster prevention and relief lies in immediate disposal and pre-disaster preparation. The Disaster Prevention and Response Team can simultaneously receive CCTV footage of underground tunnels, conduct on-site rescue connections, video conferences, meteorological information, disaster information statistics, and wireless briefings. Through intelligent system integration and upgrading, preventive measures such as measuring ditches and dredging, pruning roadside trees, etc. before disasters occur, and disaster relief equipment such as grab trucks, trucks, and chainsaws deployed on standby, actively prepare for disaster prevention and response to various disaster rescue work.\\n",
