        "Sectors most exposed^": "Education|Human health and social work activities",
        "Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "The mountainous land area in Taichung City accounts for 70% of the total, and the soil and water conservation of mountainous land is closely related to the protection of forest resources. Overutilization of forestry land leads to the Loss of green space/green cover and has a wide impact on the environment and society such as：\\n1.\\tDestroying ecosystems: Illegal deforestation and excessive use of forest land can lead to the destruction of ecosystems and the loss of biodiversity. As forests are habitats for many species, including rare and endangered species, illegal activities damage forest structure and biodiversity, and disrupt ecological balance.\\n2.\\tWater resource issue: Forest land plays an important role in protecting water resources. Illegal activities may lead to soil erosion, river pollution, and damage to water sources. This will have a negative impact on the water supply and daily life of nearby communities.\\n3.\\tClimate change: Forests are one of the largest carbon sinks on Earth which absorbs carbon dioxide and mitigating climate change. Illegal logging and excessive use of forest land lead to large-scale deforestation and destruction, releasing a large amount of carbon and exacerbating global warming issues.\\n4.\\tSocio-economic impact: Illegal use of forest land may lead to infringement of land use rights and deprive legitimate landowners of their rights and interests. In addition, illegal logging and excessive utilization can also lead to a reduction in employment opportunities, a decrease in community income, and a breakdown in the livelihoods of local residents, which may lead to social instability, conflicts, and an increase in illegal economic activities.\\n5.\\tHindering sustainable development: The excessive use of forestry land violates the principle of sustainable development. Legitimate forestry management and protection measures aim to ensure the sustainable use of forest land while maintaining ecological balance and social interests. Illegal logging and excessive utilization hinder the development of sustainable forestry, impede the long-term sustainability of resources, and put off the sustainability of the socio-economic system.\\n",
