        "Factors that affect ability to adapt": "Access to education",
        "Degree to which this factor challenges/supports the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "Supports: Somewhat supports",
        "Describe how the factor supports or challenges the adaptive capacity of your jurisdiction": "(Offering Courses to Cultivate Green-Collar Talent)\\nIn response to the rapid development of technology and industry, the skills required by the labor market are constantly evolving. Possessing digital tools and cross-disciplinary capabilities is crucial for enhancing workplace competitiveness. In response to the industrial restructuring and shifting skills requirements driven by climate change, the government is offering vocational training and skills certification programs in emerging fields such as green energy technology, environmental management, and sustainable design. These programs not only enhance participants' skills and competitiveness, but also prepare them for new positions created by the green transformation. This reduces the risk of unemployment due to skills gaps and contributes to promoting industrial upgrading and overall employment stability in society.\\n"
