      {
        "question_text": "Report the total quantity of food that is procured (in tonnes) for government-owned and/or operated facilities (including municipal facilities, schools, hospitals, youth centers, shelters, public canteens, prisons etc.). If available, please provide a breakdown per food group.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Response",
        "Total quantity of food procured (tonnes)": 18436.7,
        "Breakdown of procured food by food group": "1.\\t18,300 tons: Regarding the supply of school lunch ingredients, schools at all levels in this city have been logging in to the Ministry of Education's ingredient registration platform in accordance with regulations every day. However, the platform managed by the Ministry of Education is aimed at real-time disclosure of campus meal information and gathering information on ingredient history, and has not yet been able to provide big data analysis on the purchase or usage of ingredients.\\n2.\\t136.7 tons:\\nTaichung Home of Philanthropy\\nFresh agricultural and fishery ingredients (meat, fruits and vegetables, etc.)\\nGroceries (rice, oil, salt, sauce, vinegar, dried goods)\\nFood Bank\\nStaple foods: noodles, ramen, Guanmiao noodles, instant noodles in bowls, baby porridge, cereal bars.\\nCooking oils and seasonings: cooking oil, soy sauce, salt.\\nSweet soups and drinks: Ten Grain Treasures, oatmeal drinks, soy milk, long-lasting milk.\\nInstant sachets: sesame paste, nut drinks, instant milk cereal drinks.\\nCooking items: beef prep packs, corn soup, chicken prep packs, pork prep packs, vegetarian prep packs.\\nCanned foods: corn kernels, meat floss, potato gluten, canned mushrooms/bamboo shoots, vegetarian melon and pork, vegetarian salad sauce, vegetarian shimeji floss, zucchini, vegetable tuna, braised eel, mackerel in tomato sauce, meat sauce.\\n",
        "Year data applies to": 2025.0,
        "Comment": "1.\\tIn order to maintain the health and safety of students, schools should comply with regulations such as the \\'School Health Act\\', \\'Hygiene Management of School Canteen Kitchenware and Student Consumer Cooperative\\', \\'School Lunch Food Content and Nutritional Standards\\', etc., to ensure that the design of school lunch menus meets the nutritional needs of students. Based on the daily intake of 140 grams of vegetables, 80 grams of tofu, fish, eggs, and meat, 140 grams of fruits, and 90 grams of whole grains and miscellaneous grains for each student, and considering that there are approximately 250,000 students in municipal high schools, primary and secondary schools in this city, with 200 days of meals per academic year, the required food intake is approximately 7,000 tons of vegetables, 4,000 tons of tofu, fish, eggs, and meat, 2,800 tons of fruits (estimated at two servings per person per week), and 4,500 tons of whole grains and miscellaneous grains, totaling 18,300 tons.\\n2.\\tTaichung Home of Philanthropy provides 60.7tons; The food bank provides 76 tons and purchases 7,200 sets of supplies per month, totaling approximately 8 items; The supplies are used to distribute monthly to households receiving assistance from the Food Bank in this city. In addition, the Social Bureau's Family Welfare Service Center, Domestic Violence and Sexual Assault Prevention Center, and various district offices are open to apply for emergency food packages."
      }
