        "Base year^": 2021.0,
        "Metric value in base year^": 0.44,
        "Target year^": 2030.0,
        "Metric value in target year^": 2.0,
        "Metric value in most recent year data is available": 0.68,
        "Percentage of target achieved relative to base year (auto-calculated)^": 15.38,
        "If target type is renewable energy: Percentage of total energy that is renewable in target year": 20.0,
        "Is this target publicly available?": "Other: https://pse.is/64ax3n",
        "Progress made towards target": "1.\\tThe construction of solar photovoltaics in this city is limited by terrain restrictions, with the main goal of building \\'rooftop solar photovoltaics\\'. The city government actively develops photovoltaics through a dual strategy of regulation and rewards, and is committed to promoting green net-zero transformation. By 2024, the installed capacity has reached812.137MW.\\n2.\\tTaichung City has been allocated a total of 1,100MW of installation capacity in the first and second phases of offshore wind power generation block development. All of them are expected to be completed and connected to the grid in 2029. After the commercial transfer, the annual renewable energy power generation in Taichung City is expected to increase by 5.2 billion. It is expected to achieve the 2030 net-zero carbon emission target. As block development continues to advance, Taichung City's total offshore wind power allocated capacity is expected to reach 3GW by 2035.\\n*The development of renewable energy is a key project promoted by Taichung City. It continues to cooperate with the central government's policies to increase the amount of renewable energy power generation, hoping to increase the proportion of renewable energy power generation year by year. However, renewable energy improvement does not happen overnight and must be done step by step. According to the current national overall energy policy, it is only planned that the proportion of renewable energy will reach 27%~30% in 2030, and will increase to 60%~70% in 2050. Taichung City is actively promoting the possibility of diversifying the development of renewable energy. The utilization rate of renewable energy is expected to reach 70% in 2050.\\n"
