        "Year of formal approval of plan": 2011.0,
        "End of year plan": 2028.0,
        "Comment": "District requisition of the original site of Shuinan Airport\\nThere are 67 hectares of Taichung Central Park in the area. Hundreds of smart street lamps are installed on the park footpaths to provide sufficient nighttime lighting for the park, taking into account environmental comfort, smart and convenient management and maintenance. The smart street lamp is managed by the smart system, which can independently control the fault detection and light on and off time of each smart street lamp. and according to the illumination requirements of the park management, the dimming performance can be 0%~100%, and the light field atmosphere of each area can be set flexibly, so as to fully save manpower management costs.\\nhttps://cpark.taichung.gov.tw/main_site/main.php?main_id=401&event_id=1\\n\\nThe vast space of the park uses many green plants to present different landscapes. There are 106 species of trees, with a number of more than 11,938, of which native trees account for 83%, presenting an urban oasis that is diverse and suitable for biological habitat. The vast Matcha Lake in the park has both urban flood detention and climate regulation functions.\\nFengfu project district requisition\\nThis place was originally a military idle armored vehicle maintenance camp. In this case, a total of about 200 original trees in the camp are preserved, and some old trees with a standard diameter at breast height were retained in the Green Space 20 and 21, providing a green resting environment for the people.\\nDistrict requisition of land in the Qianzhu area of Wuri\\nIn this case, a total of 776 old trees are preserved, and 3 old Autummn Maple Trees are specially protected. Among them, 2 old Autummn Maple Trees of 300 years old are located in Qinnong Lane, Qianzhuli, which the city government aims to preserve in situ for establishing the integrity of ecological habitat. \\nIn the Qianzhu requisition case, a total of 4 underground flood detention ponds are planned, and the space on the ground is used as a landscape park. In this case, the basement beam-column design was adopted for the 4 flood detention ponds. They all meet the needs of the outflow control plan. The stored water can be used for people's livelihood in an emergency, and the remaining part is used for watering flowers and plants in green spaces to implement the effective utilization of water resources. The cost required is included in the development cost of the requisition.\\n"
