        "Year of formal approval of plan": 2024.0,
        "End of year plan": 2030.0,
        "Comment": "Urban parking spaces are insufficient and land resources are limited, making it difficult to obtain parking lots. To effectively utilize idle parking spaces at night or on holidays, parking spaces are provided to surrounding residents during off-peak hours to solve regional parking problems. Therefore, through open sharing, we can encourage municipal agencies and schools at all levels to release existing parking spaces for public use on a periodic basis, thereby increasing local parking supply, reducing the large-scale development of multi-story parking lots, alleviating the problem of insufficient parking demand among the public, and implementing the city's relevant policies on sharing parking resources."
