        "row_order": 7,
        "row_name": "Waste management",
        "Response": "Yes",
        "Provide an attachment to the strategy addressing emissions from consumption of the most relevant goods and services": "上傳_8.3_waste management_SDG 12.pdf",
        "Provide a link, if applicable, and highlight any specific action the jurisdiction is implementing to reduce emissions from the consumption of goods and services in this category": "1.\\tSpecific actions for SDG 12 indicators are as follows:\\n(1) Continue to promote plastic reduction and resource recycling and sustainable production: According to Article 18 of the Taichung Autonomous Regulations for Developing a Low-Carbon City, the bureau has announced on October 30, 2020 and banned the use of Polystyrene drink cups (including their composite materials) from January 1, 2021. It will continue to strengthen the promotion of chain beverage stores to provide preferential measures for bringing their cups establish a recycling cup service mechanism, and guide beverage stores to comprehensively replace Polystyrene cups with other materials. In addition, strengthens publicity on the public to cooperate in recycling and develop the consumption habits of bringing their tableware and shopping bags, to reduce the generation of disposable waste. Starting from October 1, 2023, beverage store operators (chain and non-chain) within the jurisdiction have been restricted from using plastic material for disposable beverage cups.\\n(2) The resource recovery rate for general waste will reach 65% by 2030: The city's resource recovery rate has been increasing year by year. According to statistics, the resource recovery rate for general waste in Taichung City in 2024 will be approximately 66.15%, and the amount of general waste recovered will be approximately 941,252 metric tons, which is equivalent to a reduction of approximately 1,938,979 metric tons of carbon emissions. (According to the Ministry of Environment's Taiwan Carbon Footprint Information Network, recycling 1 kilogram of resource waste reduces approximately 2.06 kilograms of carbon emissions).\\n(3) To ensure that the bottom slag of incineration plants is properly reused in engineering projects during the life cycle of waste, in compliance with legal regulations and without harming human health and the environment, and to achieve zero waste in resource recycling, the \\'Taichung City Waste Incineration Plant Bottom Slag Resource Recycling Product Use Management Autonomous Regulations\\' are formulated. It is required that government agencies and public units within the jurisdiction that use CLSM in public works should use local resource recycling products to replace at least 50% of granular materials, to achieve 100% local reuse of bottom slag.\\n"
