        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Permeable - Green Infrastructure for Sponge Cities: With the increasing likelihood of sudden, heavy rainfall in recent years, the concept of \\'sponge city\\' represents a city's ability to store, drain, and filter pollutants, while also providing cooling capabilities. It is a goal pursued by advanced cities. The Construction Bureau, through a three-in-one project combining pipe reduction, pedestrian-oriented walkways, and road leveling, is creating \\'breathing\\' sidewalks. These allow water and air to flow through the permeable pavement and recharge the groundwater, mitigating the heat island effect and further embodying the \\'sponge city\\' spirit in Taichung. By 2024, a total of 37 kilometers of permeable sidewalks will have been constructed and improved, including improvements to the Liren Junior High School sidewalk in Taichung's North District, the Gancheng Transportation Terminal in the Central District, the Wuquan South Road sidewalk in the South District, the Wuquan West Road Section 2 sidewalk in the Nantun District, and the Zhongzheng Road sidewalk in the Fengyuan District.\\n\\nTaichung Mayor Lu Shiuyan's commitment to creating a safe and convenient pedestrian environment has recently been recognized in international competitions! According to a report by The Economist and published in the journal Nature Cities, Taichung City ranked among the top 50 cities worldwide for walkability, with a population of over 500,000. It also ranked fourth in Asia, surpassing Tokyo, Japan, to become an internationally recognized pedestrian-friendly city. The Construction Bureau stated that the study indicated that Taichung's sidewalk suitability reached a record high of 83%, demonstrating the city government's efforts to improve the pedestrian environment have been effective.",
