        "Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Extreme heat",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Due to the abnormal climate change caused by global warming, it is common to have high temperatures both domestically and internationally. The season with high outdoor temperatures is the peak period for emergency medical treatment of heat-related illnesses. Workers who frequently engage in outdoor activities such as construction, road repairs, pole maintenance, food delivery, or farming, are particularly at high risk of experiencing heat exhaustion, Heat stress, and fainting. Furthermore, factors such as environmental wind speed, air temperature, humidity, radiant heat, personal physiological heat load, thermal regulation ability, and other external heating pressure factors are all factors that affect the health of outdoor workers. Therefore, it is necessary to raise awareness and strengthen relevant preventive measures to protect the safety and health of outdoor workers.\\nFor high-risk businesses that require workers to engage in outdoor work (such as construction projects, food delivery workers, etc.), special supervision and inspection shall be conducted annually to urge employers who violate laws and regulations to make improvements to comply with legal requirements.\\nOrganize an annual outdoor work heat hazard prevention promotion meeting to enhance employers' awareness and disaster prevention capabilities regarding the heat hazards of outdoor high-temperature work.\\nTo strengthen the health protection of outdoor workers and prevent heat diseases caused by high-temperature environments, the Occupational Safety and Health Administration of the Ministry of Labor has formulated the \\'Guidelines for the Prevention of Heat Hazards in High-Temperature Outdoor Workers\\', providing a reference for employers of high-risk outdoor heat hazards and enhancing the risk prevention and response capabilities of public institutions.\\nTo assist public institutions in implementing relevant prevention and management of heat hazards, the Occupational Safety and Health Administration of the Ministry of Labor has commissioned the establishment of the \\'High-Temperature Outdoor Work Heat Hazard Prevention Action Information Network\\' (website: https://hiosha.osha.gov.tw/content/info/index.aspx ). Through intelligent methods such as GPS positioning, weather data information of the workplace can be obtained online to calculate the heat index in real-time, and corresponding management measures, heat disease disposal methods, and information on nearby medical institutions could be provided for public institutions to evaluate and take relevant response measures, to effectively improve their heat hazard prevention and management.\\n",
