        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "1.\\tCombining with our Facebook fans page - Health Satellite, the treatment methods for high and low temperatures, Heat stress, cold health care methods, and how to supplement water, and strengthen the promotion of preventing cold and heat injuries will be promoted.\\n2.\\tDuring extreme temperature periods, in collaboration with the National Health Agency, the Central Weather Bureau, and the Academia Sinica, the \\'Lehuo Meteorological APP\\' combines information on the impact of climate on health. From time to time, during climate change, limited time motion picture cards are posted on our Facebook fans page - Health Satellite to remind the public of self-protection precautions against cold waves and heat injuries.\\n3.\\tProvide relevant information on self-protection education and promotion of air quality pollution on the website of the Municipal Health Bureau, and cooperate with the Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau to issue a warning of deteriorating air quality. Conduct timed dynamic health education and promotion on the Municipal Health Bureau's Facebook \\'Health Satellite\\'. （ https://www.health.taichung.gov.tw/1978968/post ）.\\n4. To protect the lung health of the public, the Department of Health will continue to promote the provision of pulmonary function screening services from 2019 to 2023 as a frontline preventative measure for lung health, while also strengthening public awareness and prevention of lung diseases. Furthermore, starting in 2022, in collaboration with the National Health Administration, the Department will promote publicly funded lung cancer screenings. Low-dose computed tomography (CT) scans will be offered to high-risk individuals with a family history of lung cancer (males aged 45 to 74 or females aged 40 to 74) and heavy smokers (50 to 74 years with a smoking history of 20 pack-years or more), aiming to facilitate early detection and treatment.\\n\\n",
