        "Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Drought|Extreme heat",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "The heat and humidity brought about by climate change promote the growth of bacteria, increase the difficulty of food storage, and the chance of food contamination. Dry climate poses great challenges to obtaining clean water sources and keeping food clean; To prevent food poisoning incidents caused by contamination of ingredients or water sources, the Health Bureau strengthens food safety awareness among businesses and consumers through hygiene training and the use of online communities to maintain public health.\\n1. Strengthen the drought response capability of food industry operators\\n(1) Combining the Facebook fans page and LINE group of the Food and Drug Safety Department, we will guide operators to implement drought preparedness operations, reserve sufficient water sources as soon as possible, install water storage equipment, and reserve at least \\'3 days\\' of basic water consumption to ensure the stability, safety, and hygiene of campus food supply.\\n(2) To cope with the drought situation, emergency water supply mechanisms will be provided to food container operators with insufficient water storage during the water restriction period. Operators will also be advised to adjust their menus, reduce the use of excessive water for dishes, and implement equipment cleaning and disinfection measures. Relevant water restriction measures will be implemented accordingly.\\n(3) After the restoration of the water supply, strengthen the promotion of water quality monitoring among operators, and pay attention to the cleaning of pipelines and water storage equipment to prevent cross-contamination.\\n2. Strengthen the hygiene management of water station operators to ensure the safety of drinking water\\n(1) During non-drought periods, conduct scheduled inspections and water quality sampling monitoring of water stations in various administrative districts of this city; During the drought period, enhance the hygiene and safety inspection and water quality sampling capacity of the water station to ensure the hygiene of the water supply.\\n(2) To strengthen the implementation of self-sanitation management by businesses and to unite businesses towards global sustainable development goals, the Food and Drug Safety Administration has joined hands with the Taichung City Bottled Drinking Water Business Association to strengthen businesses' awareness of regulations and sanitation management, promote the concepts of clean water and sanitation, and encourage businesses to implement self-inspections. At the same time, the Association continues to educate the public that when purchasing drinking water from coin-operated water filling stations, they should pay attention to the cleanliness of the containers to reduce the chance of water contamination, ensure that the public has clean and safe drinking water, and implement the goals of SDG6: Clean Water and Sanitation.\\n",
