        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "To reduce boiler pollution emissions, the city established the \\'Taichung City Boiler Air Pollutant Emission Standards\\' in 2017, which encourages businesses to use clean fuels such as weather gas when installing or replacing boilers and other equipment. Of the 181 boilers in this city that have been subject to stricter emission standards, 112 have been converted to gas boilers, while the remaining 69 have been dismantled, converted to diesel boilers, or have already met emission standards. In addition, there were originally 7 coal-fired boiler operators within the jurisdiction. By strengthening inspection and control and providing guidance, we have promoted the transformation of coal-fired industrial boiler fuels in the city to other solid fuels or natural gas. Currently, the remaining Zhenglong Houli Factory's pulverized coal boiler (M04) has not been improved, while the remaining boilers have been improved and will continue to guide operators for improvement. \\n*The shift to consumption of low-carbon fuels is a policy formulated for the city government. It is for internal reference only and has no public information.\\n",
