        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Promote the digitization of land administration and cross institutional services\\nFor simple registration cases, encourage the public to prioritize online application methods to increase the proportion of online registration cases. If it is not possible to apply for the case online, the public is provided with the option to choose a nearby land administration office to apply for handling matters, without the need to go to the original land administration office, saving time and reducing carbon emissions from travel.\\nThe calculation method is as follows: Convert the total number of land (building) registration cases applied for by local residents across offices to reduce the carbon emissions caused by the total distance traveled for business trips. Assuming that each applicant travels a total of 20 kilometers back and forth in a single self-use small vehicle to deliver documents, and uses the self-use gasoline small vehicle's fuel consumption (9.2km/L) and PM2.5 emission coefficient of 2.263 (kg CO2e/L) in the urban area as the basis for carbon reduction calculation, the estimated target carbon reduction amount per year (t)=total number of land (building) registration cases applied for across offices x 20 (km)/9.2 (km/L) x 2.263kg (CO2e/L)/1000\\nhttps://jsland.land.taichung.gov.tw/content/?type_id=11003&parent_id=11003\\n",
