        "Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Stationary energy: Action to to advance net zero carbon municipal buildings",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Preservation of the original location of legal buildings within the scope of district requisition\\nWithin the development scope of the section, if the development of existing legal buildings does not affect public facilities, the public can apply for the preservation of the original location, which not only allows the public to enjoy the improved public facilities after development without relocation but also avoids the generation of waste and increased carbon emissions caused by the demolition of buildings, to achieve the effect of carbon reduction.\\nThe calculation method is as follows: carbon reduction area x reduction of demolition waste disposal per floor area unit.\\nRefer to the amount of waste generated from the demolition of building units with a floor area in Kaohsiung City of approximately 1.28 t/m2, and the unit carbon emission coefficient of 2.06 tCO2e/t on the website of Ecolife-reduces the amount of waste disposal by at least one kilogram per person per day of Executive Yuan, the carbon reduction amount (t) per unit floor area reduced by demolition waste disposal is 1.28 × 2.06=2.64 tCO2e/m2.\\nIn the 2025 Taichung City Wuri-Mianchizhu District Expropriation Project, the total number of legally designated buildings eligible for retention in their original locations was assessed to be 4, with a total floor area of 712.15 m2. The total carbon reduction was calculated as 712.15 m2 x 2.64 t/m2 = 1,880.08 tCO2e. In the 2025 Taichung City Wuri-Jiude District Expropriation Project, the total number of legally designated buildings eligible for retention in their original locations was assessed to be 10, with a total floor area of 1,352.25 m2. The total carbon reduction was calculated as 1,352.25 m2 x 2.64 t/m2 = 3,569.94 tCO2e.\\nhttps://www.land.taichung.gov.tw/content/?parent_id=123581&type_id=123581\\n",
