        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "1.\\tRice Straw Cutting and Burning Prevention Program - Subsidies are provided to encourage farmers to avoid burning rice straw and instead cut it, bury it, or bundle it for transportation. This reduces air pollution from straw burning. In 2023, a total of 10,357 hectares of land were covered, reducing PM2.5 emissions by 1.72 tons. In 2024, a total of 12,441 hectares of land were covered through both guidance and voluntary cutting, reducing PM2.5 emissions by 2.07 tons.\\n2.\\tOrganic Agriculture Production Guidance Program-Switching from traditional farming to organic farming can reduce approximately 17 metric tons of CO2 per hectare per year. Through the Taichung City Organic Rice for School Lunch Program, increasing subsidies for organic verification fees, and cooperating with the Ministry of Agriculture's Agriculture and Grain Administration to implement relevant organic agriculture production guidance programs, this bureau encourages farmers to engage in organic agriculture farming.\\n3.\\tTaichung City's Domestic Organic Fertilizer Enhancement Subsidy Program - Switching from chemical fertilizers to organic fertilizers can help reduce greenhouse gas emissions, promote sustainable agricultural development, and improve soil health.\\nhttps://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1vc6NTwtvqPtAtTxYXfTqIgnFqQ2B5BZR\\n",
