        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "1. The city's Community Nutrition Promotion Centre promotes low-carbon eating through various media, including group nutrition education sessions, booths at large-scale events, radio stations, and the Department's Facebook page. It also encourages the public to use seasonal local ingredients, opt for minimal packaging and original foods, and adopt energy-efficient cooking practices, in order to create a sustainable and healthy eating environment. The city's Community Nutrition Promotion Center promotes low-carbon diets through marketing channels such as group nutrition education courses, MRT car advertisements, and online media. It also encourages the public to choose seasonal local ingredients, simple packaging and original foods, and energy-saving cooking principles in order to create a sustainable and healthy eating environment. \\n2. The city encourages catering businesses to adopt the National Health Administration's definition of healthy meal boxes: (1) whole grains, vegetables, beans, fish, eggs, and meat; (2) provide unrefined whole grain rice or unrefined grains such as pumpkin and sweet potato; (3) reduce fried foods and processed foods; (4) do not provide sugary drinks; or (5) use iodized salt and reduce salt consumption. By improving the cooking methods and ingredients used by businesses, low-carbon diets can be promoted. \\n3. By 2025, the city will continue to collaborate with 668 catering businesses to offer menus that adhere to health principles (reducing fried and processed foods, not offering sugary drinks, providing unrefined grains, and reducing sugar in product formulas). These businesses will also be included in the \\'Taichung City Sports and Healthy Dining Map\\' for public use (https://www.health.taichung.gov.tw/1792502/1792654/1792707/Lpsimplelist).\\n",
