    "q2_1_1": [
      {
        "question_text": "Provide details on your climate risk and vulnerability assessment.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Row 1",
        "Assessment attachment^": "Taipei City Climate Change Adaptation Implementation Program (2024-2026).pdf",
        "Assessment direct link^": "Taipei City Climate Change Adaptation Implementation program (2024-2026)\\nhttps://service.cca.gov.tw/File/Get/cca/zh-tw/KgVP9YuDEiStqN0",
        "Confirm attachment/link provided to assessment": "The assessment has been attached",
        "Boundary of assessment relative to jurisdiction boundary^": "Same - covers entire jurisdiction and nothing else",
        "Year of publication or approval": 2024.0,
        "Factors considered in assessment": "A process has been established to update the assessment at least every five years|A process has been established for prioritizing identified hazards|Assessment includes a high-emissions scenario (i.e., RCP 8.5)|Assessment considers nature|Identified hazards have been incorporated into the jurisdiction's overall risk management framework|Assessment considers water security|Assessment considers vulnerable populations",
        "Please explain": "Our city, following the National Climate Change Adaptation Framework, has adopted a two-stage, six-dimension approach based on national adaptation scenarios to develop and revise its implementation plan. The two stages are \\'Identifying Climate Risks and Adaptation Gaps\\' and \\'Adaptation Planning and Action,\\' while the six dimensions include \\'Defining the Scope,\\' \\'Reviewing Current Conditions,\\' \\'Assessing Risks,\\' \\'Integrating Decisions,\\' \\'Promoting Implementation,\\' and \\'Review and Adjustment.\\'\\nThe plan takes into account the city's natural environment and socio-economic development characteristics, conducting climate change impact analysis and assessments to identify key issues that require early attention, such as \\'heavy rainfall,\\' \\'high temperatures,\\' and \\'drought.\\' During the first stage, \\'Identifying Climate Risks and Adaptation Gaps,\\' the scope of adaptation is defined, current conditions are reviewed, and risks are assessed. Existing adaptation measures are evaluated against future climate risk scenarios to identify adaptation gaps.\\nIn the second stage, \\'Adaptation Planning and Action,\\' the city integrates decision-making, promotes implementation, and conducts reviews and adjustments. This process includes reviewing and integrating existing policies and related plans. Based on the city's current conditions and climate change impact analysis, the plan is tailored to the local context and focuses on six major areas: \\'vital infrastructure,\\' \\'water resources,\\' \\'land use,\\' \\'energy supply and industry,\\' \\'agricultural production and biodiversity,\\' and \\'health,\\' along with \\'capacity building.\\' The plan serves as the framework for driving the city's adaptation implementation plan, setting climate change adaptation goals, strategies, and actions across different sectors and agencies.\\n"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Provide details on your climate risk and vulnerability assessment.",
        "row_order": 3,
        "row_name": "Row 3",
        "Assessment attachment^": "Taipei City Climate Change Adaptation Plan(2012).pdf",
        "Assessment direct link^": "Taipei City Climate Change Adaptation Plan(2012)\\nhttps://www-ws.gov.taipei/Download.ashx?u=LzAwMS9VcGxvYWQvMzYzL3JlbGZpbGUvMTY5NTIvMTEyMzczLzUzY2ViZTQ5LTZmYjQtNDAyZi04YTlhLTUyMDIxOTg2ZjA3MC5wZGY%3d&n=6Ie65YyX5biC5rCj5YCZ6K6K6YG36Kq%2f6YGp6KiI55WrLnBkZg%3d%3d&icon=..pdf ",
        "Confirm attachment/link provided to assessment": "The assessment has been attached",
        "Boundary of assessment relative to jurisdiction boundary^": "Other: The scope includes the neighboring cities: New Taipei City",
        "Year of publication or approval": 2012.0,
        "Factors considered in assessment": "Assessment considers water security|Assessment includes a high-emissions scenario (i.e., RCP 8.5)|Identified hazards have been incorporated into the jurisdiction's overall risk management framework|Assessment considers nature|Assessment considers transition risks",
        "Please explain": "Human activities consume a lot of fossil fuels and forest resources, and disrupt the Earth's natural environment system and greenhouse gas circulation mechanism, leading to global warming and climate changes, and causing extreme climate events significantly increased. United Nations Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Changes Committee (IPCC) reports also pointed out that, since the 1950s, the Earth's warming and human activities are highly related (more than 90%). However, the implementation of mitigation strategies, which is reducing greenhouse gas emissions, will not be able to immediately improve the climate change impacts (carbon dioxide in the atmosphere remnants subsequent impact will continue for 50 to 200 years). Therefore, in addition to continued commitment to energy-saving and greenhouse gas emissions mitigation strategy, how to change through social and economic development patterns, prompting humans to adapt to the impacts of climate change, reduce the level of impacts of climate change, and in order to survive in the extreme climate effects, it is equally important to mitigate strategies.This project is sponsored by the Council for Economic Planning and Development, and using Taipei city as the demonstration area. The concept of strategic planning, rolling wave planning, and bottom-up approach are used in the whole planning process. Many seminars, meetings of the working platform fully with the Taipei City Government are conducted to communicate and coordinate with different sectors in the city government to get the consensus. The main project content are: (1) to establish the climate change adaptation planning framework and platform; (2) to analyzes the trends and the impact of climate change; (3) to clarify the impact of climate change in key sector with the concept of Vulnerability; (4) analysis the impact of climate change vulnerability;(5) analysis of the key issues; (6) review both policy and related programs;(7) proposal of climate change adaptation strategy and action plan.More than 40 times of meetings, seminars, and interviews were held in ten months, through the system analysis approach, this project made a total of 185 action plans. Four action plans have co-benefit with six other sectors. 162 action plans have co-benefit with at least one other sector. Only 8 action plans have trade-off with other sector. This project is a preliminary project for the first year, and should be continued in the future rolling reviewed and included in the annual implementation policy."
      }
    ],
