        "Further documentation, links and comments": "Taipei City conducts a city-level, voluntary greenhouse gas (GHG) inventory, summarized in the “GHG Emissions Analysis Report.” Total emissions decreased from 13.074 million tCO2e in 2005 to 11.955 million tCO2e in 2013, then gradually increased to 12.616 million tCO2e in 2017. Following the implementation of energy-saving and carbon reduction measures, GHG emissions have steadily declined. \\nIn 2024, total city-wide emissions were 10.5381 million tCO2e, calculated using the 2024 electricity emission factor of 0.474 kgCO2e/kWh. This represents a reduction of approximately 2.5355 million tCO2e (19.39%) compared to the 2005 baseline.\\nComparing 2024 to 2023, emissions decreased by 393,400 tCO2e (3.6%). Total electricity consumption slightly increased by 196 million kWh in 2024 due to the shift from fossil-fuel transport to low-carbon electric vehicles. Despite this increase in electricity use, reduced fossil fuel consumption and a lower electricity emission factor (from 0.494 kgCO2e/kWh in 2023 to 0.474 kgCO2e/kWh in 2024) contributed to the net decline in total city-wide GHG emissions."
