        "Climate hazards that goal addresses^": "Extreme heat",
        "Base year of goal (or year goal was established if no base year)^": 2023.0,
        "Target year of goal^": 2027.0,
        "Description of metric / indicator used to track goal and evidence of implementation": "Strengthening Community Disaster Awareness and Resilience\\n1.Enhance Community Disaster Awareness: Raise residents' understanding of disaster risks and emergency preparedness.\\n2.Foster Community Cohesion: Encourage residents to participate in disaster prevention efforts, cultivating self-help and mutual assistance capabilities, while connecting neighboring institutions such as schools, volunteer organizations, long-term care facilities, and businesses to jointly engage in disaster resilience initiatives.\\n3.Identify and Assess Potential Risks: Evaluate potential community disaster risks and prioritize interventions based on available community resources and capacities, implementing measures to enhance overall resilience.\\n4.Promote Mechanism Development: Through resilient community initiatives, enable local districts (townships, cities, or districts) to establish a mechanism for independently managing community-based disaster preparedness.\\n5.Sustain Autonomous Operations: Ensure that resilient communities can continue to function independently even when external resources are limited.\\n",
        "Comment": "Implementation of Community Disaster Preparedness Measures\\n1.Foundational Disaster Preparedness Work: Conduct environmental reconnaissance, establish community disaster management data, develop disaster maps, discuss disaster issues, carry out routine inspections and maintenance, and perform actual drills and exercises.\\n2.Consensus on Post-Disaster Recovery: Engage with community residents and professional technical personnel (e.g., electrical and water engineers, telecommunications providers, insurance agents, real estate professionals, or legal consultants) before disasters to discuss and establish recovery and reconstruction mechanisms. Agreements and memoranda of understanding are signed to ensure post-disaster recovery measures and goals.\\n3.Maintain Operational Mechanisms: Pre-plan community activities, schedule tasks, assign responsibilities, and review and improve procedures so that resilient communities can continuously implement disaster prevention work, reduce disaster risks, and facilitate interaction among residents, organizations, and businesses within a structured system.\\n________________________________________\\nTaipei City 2023 Resilient Taiwan Large-Scale Windstorm and Earthquake Preparedness and Collaboration Plan\\n1.Conducted 12 district office guidance and visitation meetings and four training sessions for district disaster management staff.\\n2.Surveyed and consolidated information for 290 designated evacuation shelters.\\n3.Conducted on-site surveys at 50 priority shelter schools.\\n4.Hosted two training sessions for 32 resilient communities and 60 certified disaster response specialists.\\n5.Implemented four disaster specialist training sessions, with 170 participants successfully completing the courses.\\n"
