        "Confirm attachment/link provided to plan": "The plan has been attached",
        "Boundary of plan relative to jurisdiction boundary": "Same (jurisdiction-wide) - covers entire jurisdiction and nothing else",
        "Processes for monitoring evaluation and updates of plan^": "Update: Updates to the plan are published every 1-3 years|Evaluation: Evaluation of plan takes place annually or more frequently than annually|Monitoring: Information on progress of plan is monitored and publicly reported annually or more frequently than annually",
        "Plan status/progress towards plan": "Underway - significant progress made",
        "Funding sources and financial instruments to finance plan": "Jurisdiction's own resources|Regional funds and programmes",
        "Communities and organizations engaged": "Non-governmental organisations|Vulnerable population groups|Local government (s) and/or agencies|Citizens|Business and private sector",
        "Describe if and how climate-related scenarios have informed the plan": "Taipei City climate change adaptation implementation plan, in addition to incorporating the Paris Agreement's target of limiting warming to 1.5°C, the IEA's \\'Net Zero by 2050: A Roadmap for the Global Energy Sector\\' released in 2021, referenced the IPCC's Sixth Assessment Report on Climate Change (AR6) Volumes 1 to 3 (WG 1~3) to develop other related projections and scenarios in order to formulate localized carbon reduction strategies and climate actions and this Act is enacted as a basis for urban transformation.",
        "Primary author(s) of plan^": "Relevant department within jurisdiction|Regional / state / provincial government",
        "Assessment of co-benefits, trade-offs, and synergies of actions included in plan": "Plan assesses trade-offs of actions|Plan assesses synergies of actions|Plan assesses co-benefits of actions",
        "Year of formal approval of plan^": 2021.0,
        "End year of plan": 2050.0,
        "Total cost of implementation of plan (in currency specified in 1.2)": 0.0,
        "Sectors covered by action plan": "Sewerage, wastewater management and remediation activities|Education|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Transportation and storage|Public administration and defence; compulsory social security|Agriculture|Administrative and support service activities|Forestry|Waste management|Water supply|Financial and insurance activities|Accommodation and food service activities",
        "Please explain": "In order to promote the City's net zero transformation, the City proposed the \\'Taipei City Net Zero Emission Management Autonomy Act\\' , which was revised after public hearings and consultation with various sectors. Incorporating the 2050 net zero emissions target into this Act, specifying the authorities and responsibilities of various city government agencies, introducing a \\'carbon budget\\' system, and setting up a climate transformation fund. In response to the United Nations IPCC AR6 ,the Act will be strengthened with a special chapter on adaptation. The Act is divided into 7 chapters and 55 articles.1. In order to increase the carbon reduction to 40% by 2030, with a net zero emissions target by 2050. Also, promote a \\'carbon budget\\', set carbon emission caps for various sectors.2. In order to promote industrial transformation, City will set up a climate transformation fund, which will be dedicated to climate change adaptation, greenhouse gas reduction, and taking care of the underprivileged in climate transformation to ensure fair transformation.3. It specifies that public buildings and buildings of a certain size in Taipei City should publicly label information on building energy consumption and strengthen controls from 2030 onward to improve building energy efficiency.4. From the public sector to private sector, the City government has set 2023 as the target year for electrification of public motorcycles and 2030 as the target date for electrification of urban buses and public cars as the key policy priority. Low-carbon transportation zones will be promoted gradually toreduce the amount of carbon emissions from transportation.5. The Act stipulates the reduction and banning of the use of disposable items, that the use of tableware should be paid for and completely banned, and requires public and private venues to set up environmentally friendly container recycling systems. In addition, it stipulates that existing old incinerators should be upgraded to high-efficiency green energy power plants and environmentally friendly green energy recycling parks, and carbon capture and utilization equipment should be introduced.6. The Act stipulates that the City Government should conduct studies and surveys on the City's land use,vulnerability and regularly review urban plans. https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4579962"
