        "Sectors covered by action plan": "Human health and social work activities|Sewerage, wastewater management and remediation activities|Water supply|Education|Waste management|Forestry|Conservation|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply",
        "Please explain": "Taipei City has been actively implementing reduction measures, resulting in a decrease in emissions of11.388 million metric tons of CO2e in 2020, representing a 12.9% reduction compared to the baseline year of 2005. The residential, commercial, and transportation sectors are the main sources of emissions, accounting for 74.6% and 20.6% of the city's total emissions, respectively. Emissions from the residential and commercial sectors decreased by 13.1% in 2020 compared to the baseline year, while emissions from the transportation sector decreased by 8.2%.The residential, commercial, and transportation sectors constitute the city's major carbon sources, accounting for 74.60%, 20.58%, and 2.69% of the total emissions, respectively. Together, these three sectors contribute to nearly 98% of the city's carbon emissions.Based on projections of future population and economic changes, it is estimated that without any relevant reduction measures, emissions in 2050 would reach 12.496 million metric tons of CO2e.The promotion of net-zero emissions in Taipei City is pursued through the implementation of smart zero-carbon buildings, green and low-carbon transportation, a circular economy with zero waste, and the enhancement of carbon sinks. A collaboration between the central government and public-private sectors is crucial to achieve the net-zero emissions goal. The main strategies for the three major sectors include energy efficiency inspections, disclosure, and regulations in the residential and commercial sectors, along with the integration of renewable energy and hydrogen use to achieve zero-carbon buildings. The transportation sector focuses on promoting green transportation and the adoption of electric (hydrogen) vehicles. The waste sector aims for a circular economy with zero waste and ultimately zero emissions from waste treatment facilities. The agriculture and forestry sector emphasizes afforestation to increase carbon sinks and strengthens wetland conservation to maintain carbon sequestration.By implementing these strategies, Taipei City aims to achieve its net-zero emissions goal and actively contribute to mitigating climate change."
