        "Sectors covered by action plan": "Transportation and storage|Waste management|Agriculture|Water supply|Forestry|Sewerage, wastewater management and remediation activities|Human health and social work activities|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply",
        "Please explain": "Taipei City has conducted an independent greenhouse gas inventory operation at the city level, showing a gradual decrease in emissions from 13.074 million metric tons of CO2e in 2005, in 2021, greenhouse gas emissions were 11.1426 million metric tons of CO2e, representing a reduction of approximately 1.9311 million metric tons compared to 2005, a decrease of 14.77%.The main sources of greenhouse gas emissions in the city are the residential, commercial, and transportation sectors, accounting for approximately 95% of the total emissions. To achieve energy-saving and carbon reduction goals, the city initially focused on the public sector and formulated an energy-saving plan for the Taipei City Government and affiliated agencies. The city government implemented measures to promote energy-saving and carbon reduction in the industrial and commercial sectors. These measures include energy-saving counseling, law enforcement and advocacy, incentive subsidies, and the promotion of energy-saving products. On-site inspections of energy-consuming equipment are conducted, and compliance with regulations is ensured. The promotion of energy-saving products is carried out through cooperation with various stores. In 2021, the service sector's electricity consumption decreased by 349 million kWh compared to 2020, resulting in an electricity saving rate of 3.77%.Solar photovoltaic systems have been installed on government agencies and schools, resulting in significant power generation and carbon reduction. Citizen power plants managed by civic groups have been established on city-owned buildings. Landfill sites are being transformed into energy parks, and small hydropower generation systems are being introduced. The city is also actively promoting the electrification of vehicles. An electric vehicle subsidy program has been announced, and charging stations are being constructed. The proportion of electric scooters in the city has significantly increased, and efforts are being made to establish a public bicycle system.To achieve net-zero emissions by 2050, the city government has revised environmental impact assessment regulations and promotes green building certifications. It has allocated funds for circular economy buildings and is actively promoting the concepts of an \\'agricultural city\\' and a \\'sponge city.\\'"
