        "Please explain": "In order to build a livable and sustainable city and to address the climate warming hazards caused by the greenhouse effect, Taipei City conducted a city-level greenhouse gas inventory on its own. The \\'Taipei City Energy Saving and Carbon Reduction Program\\' has been promoted in 2008, and in 2016, the \\'Taipei City Greenhouse Gas Control Implementation Plan\\' was formulated to strengthen the division of work among various competent authorities to jointly assume responsibility for greenhouse gas reduction in the City. In accordance with international climate agreements and the Greenhouse Gas Reduction and Management Act, the City formulated the \\'Taipei City Greenhouse Gas Control Implementation Plan\\' in 2019.The City's Greenhouse Gas Control Implementation Plan (Phase 1) was promoted from 2018 to 2020, and the \\'Greenhouse Gas Reduction Steering Committee\\' was established, with the mayor as the convener, to supervise the implementation of energy saving and carbon reduction action plans of four major city government sectors (residential and commercial, transportation, waste, and agriculture and forestry) every quarter, and invite experts and scholars to jointly discuss. In addition, the target of 8% reduction in greenhouse gas emissions in 2020 compared to the base year (2005) was set, and the total emissions in 2020 were 11,388,000 tons, showing a 12.9% reduction compared to the base year, achieving and exceeding the original target of 8% reduction. 1. Target to have a 20MW photovoltaic power generation equipment installation capacity in 2020: 33.63MW of cumulative installation capacity.2. Target to complete the replacement of 140,440 public streetlights with LED and other energy-saving lamps by the end of 2020: Completed the replacement of 150,930 LED streetlights in the whole City.3. Target to reach 84.51% of the population with access to wastewater treatment by the end of 2020: 85.58% of the population with access to wastewater treatment.4. Target to increase the area of green resources in the City by 250,000m2 by the end of 2020: Increased the area of green resources by about 265,000m2.5. Target to reach 66.8% of the green transportation market share by 2020: Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the percentage of public transportation ridership was affected, and the percentage of people using and taking green transportation reached 60.1%"
