        "Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Mass movement|Hurricanes, cyclones, and/or typhoons|Heavy precipitation",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Taipei City Promotion Taskforce of Flood Resilient-Resistant Community Project\\nhttps://heo.gov.taipei/cp.aspx?n=0FB7DE550257C53C\\nIn 2019, the “Taipei City Promotion Taskforce of Flood Resilient-Resistant Community Project” was initiated. A professional consultant team was entrusted to handle the advocacy and the promotion of disaster-resistant matters in the communities and on campuses. In 2019, we promoted communities located in the Dahu Village in Neihu District, Jiangshan Village in Zhongshan District, and Guangneng Village in Datong District. In 2020, we promoted the Zhonghua Village in Songshan District, Heping Village in Wanhua District, and Yide Village in Beitou District as disaster prevention demonstration communities. In 2021, we promoted Qunxian Village in Daan District, Jiying Village in Zhongshan District, and Xingwang Village in Wenshan District as disaster prevention demonstration communities.This project uses Opendata, such as flood simulation maps, flood protection plans, and rain gauges, and promotes the flood resilient disaster-resistance community project, so that community residents have the ability to respond to disasters and emergencies. Community courses on disaster prevention include at least the “composition of the disaster prevention community work team and guidance meeting,” “enlightenment and initiation of disaster prevention community,” “community diagnosis for disasters in the environment and formulation of countermeasures for issues on disaster prevention and protection,” “establishment of community disaster prevention and protection organization, task division and operation,” “community disaster prevention and protection, rescue training or seminars,” “disaster prevention personnel training and counseling,” and community emergency drills are conducted. When heavy rain is forecasted, pre-disaster preparations are carried out. When the heavy rain occurs, residents are quickly gathered for evacuation, rescue, and other emergency responses, and after the heavy rain stops, post-disaster recovery is carried out, such as cutting down the collapsed trees on the road, assisting the evacuation of disadvantaged groups, CPR and AED performance, flood gate operations, and water pump operations.In addition, Taipei City Government Hydraulic Engineering Office of the Public Works Department also refers to the analysis of flooding potential and the water accumulation events over the years before the flood period every year. For urban areas with relatively lowland and high risk of water accumulation (102 areas in 2021), mechanical water pumps are leased in advance during the typhoon and heavy rain period to reduce risks and occurrence of disasters.",
