        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Dengue Fever Prevention\\nhttps://data.taipei/dataset/detail?id=aa397ee2-9e39-44b9-9d0d-d88a16987a3f\\n1. Through the \\'Capital Living Circle Dengue Fever/Chikungunya Prevention and Control Plan,\\' our city integrates the efforts of the health, environmental protection, civil affairs, and education departments, both during normal times and when local dengue cases occur. This cross-departmental collaboration implements relevant prevention and control measures to prevent community outbreaks of dengue fever.\\n2. As of December 31, 2023, the city has collaborated with 99 medical institutions to join the \\'Dengue Fever Prevention Network, Community Clinic Rapid Screening and Reporting.\\' This facilitates the early detection and treatment of dengue fever cases and helps prevent the spread of the epidemic.\\n3.Using the Mosquito-Borne Disease Prevention Information Integration System (GIS), the city conducts surveys on mosquito density in high-risk community areas (such as vacant houses, vacant land, markets, etc.). This provides epidemic prevention personnel with disease outbreak data and related geographic information for precise prevention and control efforts.\\n4.The city recruits and trains epidemic prevention teams in all 12 districts. By localizing prevention efforts, these teams enhance community and campus dengue fever mosquito control awareness and capabilities. This ensures that they can quickly mobilize and control outbreaks during emergencies, thereby strengthening community epidemic prevention capabilities.\\n",
