        "Climate hazard(s) that action addresses": "Extreme heat",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Heatwave warning mechanism\\nhttps://www.dep.gov.taipei/News_Content.aspx?n=9086C3ED2A4F6A09&sms=9B5E42F97878D232&s=89848F0E2E80CC5C\\nThe temperature of the subtropical monsoon climate in Taipei City ranges from 16-30°C. However, it is difficult to dissipate heat in Taipei basin, which may easily cause heat island effect and raise temperature up to 35°C, and further hit record high at 39.7°C in 2020. In order to mitigate the threat of high temperature to the health of citizens, Taiwan's heat wave warning mechanism was incorporated into the regional disaster prevention and protection plan in 2016, which stipulate that the relevant institutions shall initiate response measures when standards for notification and warning are reached. There were 81 heat wave warnings in 2016-2022, and the measures and achievements of various government departments are as follows:(1) The Department of Environmental Protection uses reclaimed water for sprinkling to cool the surface temperature of roads. The temperature of asphalt pavement can reach above 50°C under high temperature, while the temperature can be reduced by 10°C after sprinkling, and reduce road dust. About 5,443km of roads was sprinkled.(2) To improve the survival rate of plants and green cover ratio, the Parks and Street Lights Office uses recycled water for plant irrigation and prevent plants from drying up under high temperature. The high vegetation cover may improve the microclimate and cool down the city. The total area of plant irrigation was 7,062,134sqm.(3) In order to prevent food poisoning and spoilage under high temperature, the Department of Health has incorporated food preservation in its routine audits and counseling, so that food companies will become more aware of the environment and temperature for preserving food and ingredients, as well as the expiry date and the implementation of hygiene management to mitigate the effect of heat wave on food. 1,715 counseling activities in the food industry, and 6,893 advocacies of food safety to markets and vendors in cooperation with the Taipei City Market Administration Office.(4) In order to prevent heat stress to outdoor workers, the Department of Labor launched the Summer Outdoor Worker Heat Stress On-Site Inspection, and urged enterprises and on-site management personnel to attach great importance in implementing the preventive measures for heat stress, such as installation of effective sun shades, water spraying systems, rest areas, and drinking water supplies. There were a total of 1,778 heat stress worker inspections.(5) The Department of Social Welfare appoints social workers and volunteers to care for the physically and mentally disabled and elderlies that live alone, and provides related heat relief equipment, notifying short-term summer shelters near the residence, in order to mitigate health risks of the disadvantaged people under extreme temperature. Up until now, it has provided care for 90,364 people, including elderlies, the disabled and homeless people.The aforementioned policies and measures are adopted to reduce the threat and negative impact of heat wave in Taipei City.",
