        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Flood and Extreme Rainfall Resilience - Feitsui Raw Water Diversion Project\\n\\nTo mitigate the risk of extreme rainfall events causing raw water turbidity levels to exceed the treatment capacity of existing purification facilities, Taipei Water Department implemented the Feitsui Raw Water Diversion Project. A new intake and dedicated pipeline, approximately 2.8 km in length, was constructed downstream of Feitsui Reservoir. This allows the diversion of up to 2.7 million tons of cleaner raw water per day from the Beishi River during periods when turbidity levels in the Nanshi River are elevated.\\n\\nThe project achieved full tunnel breakthrough on May 12, 2023, and officially commenced water delivery operations on June 20, 2024. During Typhoon Gaemi (July 2024), Typhoon Koinu, and Typhoon Kong-rey (October 2024), a total of 12.94 million tons of low-turbidity water from the Beishi River were successfully diverted and treated.\\n\\nThrough this project, Taipei City has significantly enhanced water supply stability for the Greater Taipei area, strengthened community resilience against climate-induced disasters, and contributed to advancing sustainable development goals.",
