        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "1. Promoting Voluntary Energy Conservation in the Industrial and Commercial Sectors\\n•\\tGuidance and Support: Conducted on-site energy efficiency assessments to assist industrial and commercial users in establishing energy-saving action plans and targets. In 2024, a total of 380 enterprises were guided, achieving an estimated savings of 92.39 million kWh.\\n•\\tInspection and Compliance: In accordance with Article 8 of the Ministry of Economic Affairs' Energy Management Act, inspections were carried out on 20 designated user categories. In 2024, 3,118 enterprises were audited, resulting in an estimated savings of 3.32 million kWh.\\n•\\tPromotion of Energy Conservation: Through school education, appliance exhibitions, and online marketing campaigns, the city promoted energy-saving awareness and disseminated information on subsidies for energy-efficient products, encouraging the public to adopt energy-saving appliances.\\n2. Promoting Solar PV Systems on Public Buildings and Land\\nAs of the end of 2024, the Taipei City Government has installed solar PV systems across 112 government agencies and 166 schools, with a total capacity of 49,628 kW. Including installations by central government agencies and private entities located in Taipei, the total installed capacity reached 83,556 kW, with an estimated annual generation of 84.06 million kWh.\\n",
