      {
        "question_text": "Describe any planned climate-related projects within your jurisdiction for which you hope to attract financing.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Row 1",
        "Project area": "Transport",
        "Project title": "Comprehensive promotion of green transportation",
        "Stage of project development": "Implementation",
        "Status of financing": "Project partially funded and seeking additional funding",
        "Identified financing model": "Public finance- own budget",
        "Project description and URL link, if applicable": "Taipei City is accelerating the transition from diesel to electric buses to reduce transport-related carbon emissions and improve urban air quality. By the end of 2024, 712 electric buses were already in operation, and the City targets full electrification of its urban bus fleet by 2030. To achieve this ambitious goal, additional financing is required to support large-scale bus procurement, expansion of charging infrastructure, and technical assistance programs. The project will not only cut greenhouse gas emissions but also generate co-benefits such as improved public health, reduced noise pollution, and enhanced quality of life for residents.",
        "Total cost of project (in currency specified in 1.2)": 4786777.0,
        "Total investment cost needed, if relevant (in currency specified in 1.2)": 4786777.0,
        "If this project is related to a previously reported adaptation or mitigation action, select the ID of the action": "Mitigation Action 10|Mitigation Action 13|Mitigation Action 12|Mitigation Action 18|Mitigation Action 17|Mitigation Action 15|Mitigation Action 11|Mitigation Action 14"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Describe any planned climate-related projects within your jurisdiction for which you hope to attract financing.",
        "row_order": 2,
        "row_name": "Row 2",
        "Project area": "Renewable energy",
        "Project title": "Promoting the Installation of solar energy systems in the public real estate",
        "Stage of project development": "Implementation",
        "Status of financing": "Project partially funded and seeking additional funding",
        "Identified financing model": "Public finance- own budget",
        "Project description and URL link, if applicable": "Taipei City is advancing solar and renewable energy deployment through multiple initiatives, including landfill-to-energy transformation, the Taipei Solar Rooftop Project, citizen-owned power plants, subsidy programs, and smart grid promotion. By August 2024, the City had installed solar PV systems across 108 municipal agencies and 166 schools, with a total capacity of 49.32 MW. Together with installations by central government and private entities, citywide capacity has reached 81.67 MW, generating an estimated 77.91 million kWh annually and reducing approximately 38,485 tons of CO₂ emissions.\\n\\nTo foster public participation, Taipei pioneered Taiwan's first citizen-owned solar plant on municipal property at Guandu Junior High School in 2020, and continues to open rooftop space for community-led renewable projects. The “Taipei Energy Hill” initiative, repurposing restored landfill sites such as Fudekeng Environmental Restoration Park and Nangang Shanzhulu Eco Park, has added nearly 3 MW capacity and generates 3 million kWh annually under a public-private investment model.\\n\\nIn addition, the City is piloting small hydropower systems, with the first 0.5 kW demonstration plant launched in partnership with private enterprises in 2023. These combined efforts not only enhance renewable energy generation and reduce reliance on fossil fuels but also create opportunities for community engagement, environmental education, and innovative financing models. Taipei City seeks to further scale these initiatives through external financing, ensuring long-term renewable energy resilience and contribution to the City's 2050 Net Zero pathway.",
        "Total cost of project (in currency specified in 1.2)": 2354310000.0,
        "Total investment cost needed, if relevant (in currency specified in 1.2)": 2354310000.0,
        "If this project is related to a previously reported adaptation or mitigation action, select the ID of the action": "Adaptation Action 4|Adaptation Action 3|Adaptation Action 8|Adaptation Action 1"
      }
