        "Areas collaboration focused on": "Adaptation|Resilience",
        "Description of collaboration and any progress, if applicable": "Since 2023, the Taoyuan City Government has established rooftop gardens in administrative villages with significant urban heat island effects, including Xinpu, Ruitai, Dahan, Daren, Dongxing, and Renxiang in Taoyuan, Bade, and Zhongli Districts. These rooftop gardens not only beautify the environment but also help enhance climate resilience. Through rooftop greening, buildings can reduce heat island effects, lower summer air conditioning energy consumption, and assist with rainwater retention and infiltration, thereby easing urban drainage pressure. At the same time, residents can grow vegetables and fruits in the gardens, shortening food miles, increasing local food self-sufficiency, and improving adaptive capacity during extreme weather events or supply disruptions. Such spaces also foster community interaction and environmental education, cultivating a shared sense of responsibility for maintenance and creating community environments that embody ecological, social, and sustainable values.",
