        "Description of collaboration and any progress, if applicable": "On February 15, 2023, Taiwan enacted the Climate Change Response Act, requiring local governments to implement adaptation measures. In response, Taoyuan City formally enacted the Taoyuan Self-Government Regulations for Promoting a Net-Zero City on July 25, 2025, following reassess Taoyuan City's climate change risks and complete the 'Taoyuan City Climate Change Adaptation Implementation Programs 2024', progressively addressing climate risks and vulnerabilities through regulations and strategies.\\nThe adaptation implementation plan is led by municipal agencies in collaboration with businesses and citizens. Initiatives include disaster prevention training, community-based disaster preparedness and response planning, regular education and drills, corporate adoption of tree-planting and reforestation projects, and ESG and net-zero transformation counseling. These efforts strengthen adaptive capacity, improve land-use planning, secure energy supply, and support industrial transformation. In terms of water resources, by strengthening supply resilience and improving water circulation, Taoyuan aims to ensure stable supply, promote sustainable development of livelihoods and industries, and effectively respond to extreme climate challenges. In terms of agriculture, by enhancing ecosystem service capacity, improving climate risk management, and identifying diversified opportunities under climate change, the city seeks to advance sustainable agricultural development.",
