        "Primary emissions sector addressed and action type^": "Transportation: Development of 15/30-minute neighborhoods (complete neighborhoods)",
        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "Taoyuan is advancing vehicle electrification while expanding public transportation initiatives. In July 2023, the TPASS monthly commuter pass was launched, covering Keelung, Taipei, New Taipei, and Taoyuan, and integrating intercity buses, Taiwan Railways, the Taoyuan Airport MRT, Taipei Metro and light rail, city buses, public bike systems, and Taipei River Cruise (including ferry services). The program has since been extended to the Taoyuan-Hsinchu-Miaoli region. In 2024, total public transportation ridership exceeded 109 million trips, an 11% increase from the previous year. The city also introduced the “Carbon Reduction Account” initiative, which attracted 330,000 participants. Through a point collection system, lotteries, rewards, and rankings, the program encouraged public participation and reduced dependence on private vehicles. Trips were automatically recorded via the EasyWallet app, with total reductions reaching 44,291,930 metric tons of CO₂e. Meanwhile, the YouBike system was upgraded with 600 new YouBike 2.0E e-bikes, supported by the construction of 496.7 kilometers of bike lanes. By the end of 2024, total cycling mileage reached 28.11 million kilometers. Taoyuan's shared mobility services also achieved full citywide coverage. By the end of 2024, the fleet included 1,190 shared e-scooters and 200 shared cars, attracting 978,000 and 235,000 cumulative users, respectively.",
