        "Action description and web link to further information^^": "To promote industrial transformation, in October 2023, Taoyuan joined the Powering Past Coal Alliance (PPCA) through a bilateral virtual meeting. The Alliance officially announced Taoyuan's membership at COP28. Consequently, the city's seven coal-fired cogeneration plants (11 units in total) will complete their coal phase-out by 2030. Since 2024, the city government has prohibited the issuance of new coal-use permits and has provided guidance to ensure stable energy supply during the transition. Compared with 2023, coal consumption in 2024 was reduced by 130,000 metric tons, equivalent to 312,000 metric tons of CO₂e reductions.",
